title: coconut custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie plate. Start in a cool oven.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until a knife comes out clean. Refrigerate after cooled.

title: angel food freezer cake
directions: Bake angel food cake according to the package.
Let cool completely.
Cut cake in half, making 2 layers.
Spread heavy cream, whipped, on the bottom layer.
Then put slices of peaches on top of cream.
Put top layer on and spread the remaining cream on top and sides.
Put remaining peaches on cake, then wrap thoroughly and put in freezer for 2 hours.
Take out of freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni. Cook and stir oleo, salt and pepper over medium heat. Blend in flour. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.

Boil and stir 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted. Place macaroni in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add cheese sauce and stir. Cook, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Stir Crisco and milk together; add hot water and stir until blended; add salt and flour.
This will be a soft dough and should be rolled between 2 sheets of waxed paper.

title: mexican meat pie
directions: Brown meat with onion and black pepper.
Add tomatoes and salt to taste.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half each of the tortillas, meat, beans and cheese.
Repeat.
Top with soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: grandma hoover's chili sauce
directions: Cook all together for 2 hours, then bottle, using 5 minutes hot water bath.

title: almond tea
directions: Simmer sugar, 6 cups water and lemon juice for 5 minutes. Cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.
This beverage freezes well.

title: savory rump roast with mushrooms
directions: Puncture roast with fork and sprinkle tenderizer, salts, pepper and garlic.
To seal in juices, sprinkle flour over roast.

title: egg nog bread
directions: Grease bottom of loaf pan.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, egg nog, butter, rum and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until moist.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pecan pie - georgia style
directions: Beat eggs just until mixed well.
Add syrup and milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add to egg mixture and blend until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Let stand for several hours overnight is best.
Pour into a fluted pie shell and bake at 425° until crust is brown.
Reduce to 350° heat and bake until filling is set, approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable rice ring
directions: Mix cooked rice and Italian dressing; chill 2 hours.
Add mayonnaise.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Season with salt, garlic salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Press into mold, or serve from bowl after chilling 2 to 3 hours.

title: summer tuna cakes
directions: Combine zucchini, tuna, bread cubes, lemon juice, egg and onion in a bowl.
Mix well. Shape into patties.
Fry on both sides in oil in skillet until brown.
Serve warm.

title: hot toddy
directions: Just before serving, into old-fashioned glass, measure all ingredients.
Place teaspoon in glass.
Add boiling water to fill glass.
(Teaspoon helps prevent glass from breaking when boiling water is added.)
Stir mixture.
Makes 1 serving.
Very good for cold weather; keeps the chill out.

title: gramp's chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs one at a time. In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to creamed mixture.
Put in vanilla. Mix well.
Use 3 or 4 round pans greased and lightly floured. Fill each pan 1/2 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost (recipe follows).

title: tomato sauce
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes and onions.
Remove seeds from peppers and chop.
Combine all ingredients in a large kettle and simmer for 1 hour or until thick.
Pack into hot sterilized jars.
Seal. Process for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 half-pints.

title: strawberry breakfast shake
directions: In an electric blender, place milk, strawberries, egg substitute, sugar and vanilla extract; whirl until smooth.
Yield: 2 portions, 2 1/2 cups.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Cream by hand, margarine, eggs, shortening and sugar.
Add flavorings to creamed mixture. Alternate, adding some flour and some milk as you blend with mixer until all flour and milk is used.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Bring water and salt to boil; add grits, stirring all the time.
Cover; turn to low and let grits thicken.
Remove from stove.
Cut cheese roll and margarine into pieces.
Add to grits and stir in well.
Add eggs and milk mixture; stir and blend into grits.
Pour into two baking dishes or one deep dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for almost an hour (if in deep dish) or about 45 minutes (if in 2 small ones).
Will be golden brown around the edges.

title: italian pastry
directions: In medium-size bowl, let cream cheese and butter soften. Then blend together well. Add flour and mix well. Shape into 24 small balls.
Shape into bottom of mini-greased cupcake pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine and bake at 325° until hot.

title: golden eggs
directions: Beat eggs with half and half.
Heat butter in heavy skillet. Pour in egg mixture.
Reduce heat and as mixture begins to set, lift cooked portions with spatula to allow uncooked portions to flow to bottom.
Cook until thickened but still moist.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart shallow casserole.
Combine next 3 ingredients. Spoon over eggs.
Dice bacon.
Fry until crisp; drain.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake in 250° oven, uncovered until heated through (75 to 90 minutes).
Serves 8 to 10.
Can be held up to 1/2 hour in oven without becoming tough.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread pieces in a quart casserole.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Stir into egg.
Add vanilla. Heat milk (do not boil).
Stir warm milk into egg mixture slowly. Pour mixture over bread.
Bake at 325° until tip of knife inserted into the center comes out clean, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit bread
directions: Mix sugar, bananas, eggs and pineapple.
Combine with oil. Combine flour, salt and baking soda; fold into fruit mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Grease tube pan and dust with flour.
Pour in mix.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Cool. May be frozen.

title: escalloped carrots
directions: Melt butter and Crisco in top of double boiler.
Add flour; mix well.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, until thick sauce forms.
Add cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Add carrots.

title: plum oatmeal bread(makes two loaves)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and oats.
Stir chopped plums in flour mixture to coat well. Add enough water to the plum juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Combine plum juice, eggs and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into two greased 8 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap and store overnight for flavor.

title: mom's carrot bread
directions: Cream together	the
eggs, oil and sugar.
Add carrots, pineapple (juice
and all), walnuts, raisins and vanilla.
Add flour, salt
and
soda,
beating until well mixed.	Place in 2 greased and brown paper lined 8 x 5 x 3-inch pans.	Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until done.
Great for cream cheese sandwiches.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Cooking Time: 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add in whipping cream and vanilla; fill freezer with milk.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Use fresh, firm, medium cucumbers, wash them and cut them into sticks. Pour boiling water over them and let stand overnight. Next morning, pack solidly in jars and make solution with remaining ingredients.
Bring solution to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour while boiling over cucumbers in jar.
Put on caps, screwing bands tight.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
In separate bowl, combine chopped vegetables.
In smaller bowl, mix mayo, seasoned salt, sugar and remaining ingredients.
Combine vegetables and macaroni. Pour mayo mixture over top.
Chill for a couple of hours before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend oil and 2
sugars;
stir in beaten eggs and pumpkin. Add nuts and dates.
Pour
batter
in 3 pound coffee can (greased and floured).
Cover
can
with
6 to 8 paper towels. Place lid on top.
Bake on
high
setting 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours in crock-pot.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook broccoli and onion in butter until onion is limp.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until well blended. Place in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
If desired, top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Mix other ingredients together; pour over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Dust with powdered sugar; cut when cool.

title: apricot jello
directions: Mix orange juice and lemon juice; bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O. Set aside and cool.
Beat the cream cheese in mixer for 2 minutes. Add cream cheese and peaches to Jell-O mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 11 x 2-inch dish.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6.

title: taco pizza
directions: Brown meat.
Add taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Spread refried beans onto crust, using spoon.
Top with ground meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
(At this point, you can cover with plastic wrap, not foil, and leave in refrigerator overnight. Add 5 minutes to cooking time.) Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with torn lettuce,
chopped tomato and taco sauce.

title: pastry pan casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; crumble ground beef in bottom.
Layer onion, potatoes and carrots; season.
Slice oleo over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Mix soup and water and add to mixture. Cover; bake 15 minutes more.
Unroll crescent rolls and lay on top.
Bake until brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix together. Roll out and cut. Bake until brown at 325°.

title: oven frying mix
directions: Stir ingredients together until well blended and store in a covered container (makes 2 cups).
Recipe is enough for 8 cut-up frying chickens.
Recipe adds 30 to 35 calories per serving.
For variety, add 1 tablespoon of sesame seed.

title: cranberry mincemeat pie
directions: Combine sauce and
mincemeat;
pour
into pastry shell. Combine pecans, sugar and butter; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes
or until crust is brown and filling is bubbly.
Cool on rack
at
least
1 hour before slicing.
Just before serving, heat brandy
over
low
heat.
Ignite
with
a match and pour over pie.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add caraway seed and raisins.
Stir in buttermilk to make a soft dough.
Knead dough for 1 minute.
Shape into round loaf and put in 8-inch round pan. Pat flour over top, then cut crosswise into the top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Combine milk and eggs, stir well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until pudding mixture comes to a boil. Remove pudding mixture from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla. Pour mixture into (4) 6 oz. custard cups.
Cover with plastic wrap gently pressing into pudding.
Chill at least 45 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Sift flour with soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk; beat well.
Add bananas, vanilla and pecans (chopped).
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven in 3 round cake pans.

title: ranch pudding
directions: In saucepan, mix 1 cup of brown sugar, water and butter and boil 5 minutes.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Mix 1 cup brown sugar, milk, Bisquick, dates, nuts and vanilla.
Spoon batter on top of sugar mixture and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream!

title: herbed lentils and rice
directions: Combine broth, lentils, onion, uncooked brown rice, wine, basil, salt, oregano, thyme, garlic powder, pepper and shredded Swiss cheese.
Turn mixture into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole with tight lid.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until lentils and rice are done, stirring twice.
Uncover casserole; top with cheese strips.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes more to melt cheese.
Garnish with watercress or parsley.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients and cook until tender.
Add sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook a little longer.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup of the crust mixture to thicken.

title: stuffed grape leaves
directions: Drain grape leaves.
Combine meat, rice, onions, garlic and spices thoroughly.
Wrap small portions in each grape leaf by rolling 2/3 up, then folding in both sides and finish rolling.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Put egg and water in small bowl; mix well.
Put 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper in egg mixture.
Mix. Put flour in another bowl.
Dip onion rings in egg/water mix.
Take out and roll in flour and drop in hot grease.
Cook until golden brown.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Pour beans into glass casserole dish.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in bacon bits or place raw bacon strips on top of beans.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 1 hour.
Can also be baked in microwave on high for 6-10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients except chocolate chips into mixing bowl. Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spread mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rashida's zucchini casserole
directions: Butter a large casserole; sprinkle rice over butter.
Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Chop vegetables and add all to casserole.
Sprinkle with seasoning and then with brown sugar. Dot with 3 tablespoons butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Drain chilies, cut in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Brown beef and onion, drain off fat.
Place 1/2 the chilies in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with meat mixture.
Arrange rest of chilies.
Combine all other ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Pour over chilies.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted shows done.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a jar.
Pour over salad.

title: norwegian gooey cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs by hand.
Press into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients with beater.
Spread on top of dough in pan.
Sprinkle liberally with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli in very small pieces.
Add to diced cheeses and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, salt and vinegar together.
Stir into vegetables.
Add bacon last.

title: peanut butter streusel pie
directions: Mix by hand peanut butter and powdered sugar until mealy; put 2/3 of it over the bottom of baked shell.
Take flour, sugar and salt; combine in double boiler with rest of the peanut butter mixture.
Take scalded milk; add slowly to flour mixture and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Beat 3 egg yolks and add to hot mixture slowly; cook a few minutes longer.
After done, add butter and vanilla.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taina's mini pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out each individual biscuit to desired size.
Place on nonstick cookie sheet.
Spoon pizza sauce on each.
Sprinkle each with plenty of cheese and lastly, top with sliced pepperoni or any other desired topping.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove; allow to cool slightly and enjoy.

title: shrimp etouffe
directions: Saut green onion tops, onion, celery and bell pepper in the margarine until tender. Stir in flour; slowly add water enough to make smooth consistency. Add tomato and simmer 30 minutes. Add shrimp and cook for 5 to 10 minutes. Serve over a bed of rice.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in a bowl.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken noodle salad
directions: Boil the noodles and eggs. Drain the chicken and peas. Chop or hydrate onions. Stir everything together, except peas and 2 eggs. Fold in peas and slice remaining eggs on top. Lightly sprinkle paprika on top. Refrigerate.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix.
Divide in rolls for slicing.
Freeze.
Slice 1/4 inch and bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: nancy's chicken-zucchini special
directions: Cook chicken and cut it up.
Saute diced onion in 1 to 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add chicken; cook about 3 to 5 minutes. Season to taste.
Blanche zucchini in boiling water; do not overcook.

title: caroline trifle
directions: Mix pudding according to directions, except use 2 3/4 cups of milk and 1/4 cup cooking sherry.
Alternate layers of pound cake with pudding and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit or sprinkle with nuts.

title: spicy filled peaches
directions: Drain syrup from peaches and boil 1/2 cup syrup with vinegar, cloves and 2-inch piece of cinnamon stick about 5 minutes. (There will be about 1/3 cup liquid.) Mix almonds, raisins, coconut, cherries and 1/4 cup cooked liquid and let stand about 10 minutes. Pour remaining liquid over peach halves. Put 2 peach halves together with spoonful of nut mixture in center and put a cinnamon stick through all. Chill until serving time.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine egg whites, buttermilk, vanilla, apple juice concentrate and pumpkin.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick vegetable coating.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Yields 12 muffins.
One muffin equals 1/2 fruit exchange, 1 bread exchange.

title: hearty twice-baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and pierce potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 60 minutes or microwave, uncovered on high for 12 to 14 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook the sausage over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, cut in half lengthwise; scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4 inch shell.
In a large mixing bowl, mash the pulp with butter.
Stir in the sausage, cheese, ham, bacon, sour cream, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Spoon into potato shells.
Place on two ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Yield:
16 servings.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Brown chicken on both sides. Pour soy sauce mixture and let boil. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus brunch melts
directions: Cook sausage and drain.

title: boiled cake
directions: Mix the raisins, shortening, sugar and boiling water together and boil for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and cloves together.
Add to the boiled raisins mixture.
Then bake in oven at about 375° for at least an hour.
Test with toothpick after the first 1/2 hour, so that it does not bake too fast.
Fruit and nuts can be added to the raisin mixture before adding the dry mixture.
It looks like a fruit cake when done.

title: grandma's chocolate icing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil; let boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Let stand a minute. Spread on cake.

title: turkey neck supreme
directions: Boil turkey necks with salt and pepper until almost tender. Add onions, bell pepper and carrots and continue to simmering until carrots are almost tender.
Add noodles; simmer for 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, peas and crushed red pepper.
Make a paste with flour and water.
Stir in and cook for approximately 5 minutes.
Serve with Mexican cornbread.
Quick and easy.
A complete meal for the working woman or overworked housewife!

title: apricot bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; add to sugar.
Add egg, flour and baking soda; mix well.
Then add lemon extract.
Put a large handful of dough in freezer.
Pat rest of mixture into pan and cover with preserves. Then crumble the chilled dough over the top and bake for 35 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt, Crisco and sugar in large bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in water; add yeast, beaten egg and half the flour; beat well.
Stir in flour to make dough easy to handle.
Grease top of dough.
Cover and let rise to double.
Make up to your desire.

title: sandwich pepper relish
directions: Grind onion and peppers.
Mix and drain well.
Combine flour, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Mix with onion and peppers.
Cook slowly about 12 to 15 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: 99% fat-free chicken stock
directions: Put chicken bones, vegetables and parsley in large stockpot. Cover with water.
Bring to a rapid boil over high heat, then skim the foamy residue off the top.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer for about 4 hours, uncovered, until the bones begin to disintegrate.
Periodically skim the residue off the top.
Remove the pot from heat.
Discard all solid ingredients and strain liquid into large bowl.
Add peppercorns and refrigerate, uncovered, for 2 to 3 hours.
If refrigerating overnight, cover after 2 or 3 hours. Remove stock from refrigerator and lift off layer of fat that has settled on top.
Place stock in a large pot and cook over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes, until stock has liquefied.
Pour liquefied stock through strainer lined with double layer of cheesecloth (to strain the sediment) into a clean bowl.
Chicken stock will keep for 3 days in refrigerator or 6 months in freezer.
For convenience, freeze in 2 or 4-cup portions in resealable plastic bags.

title: cherry or blueberry pie
directions: Combine and press into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: wasaka gullion(goo-yawn)
directions: Fry bacon with onion and drain.
Fry hamburger and drain.
Add bacon mix and hamburger to Spaghetti-O's.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes.
This was a favorite for the Girl Scouts to make while camping out.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Cover top with butterscotch bits. Batter will be very thick.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chocolate or peanut butter fudge
directions: Peanut Butter Fudge: Omit chocolate chips and nuts. Add 8 ounces peanut butter.

title: chinese beef and pea pods
directions: Cut meat diagonally into very thin slices.
Mix 1 tablespoon soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Sprinkle on the meat; toss. Marinate meat 1 hour.
Place frozen snow peas in colander; run cold water over peas just until separated.
Drain.
In large skillet or wok, heat 2 tablespoons oil; brown meat, stirring frequently.
Remove meat; keep warm.
Add 2 tablespoons oil; cook and stir mushrooms, celery, onion and chestnuts for 2 minutes. Stir in snow peas and 1 cup of the broth.
Cover and cook 2 minutes.
Mix remaining broth, cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and sugar; pour into skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add meat; heat through.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: hot tamales
directions: Put all ingredients except 1 can tomato sauce, 2 ounces chili powder and corn meal in roasting pan and mix well by hand.
Take about 1 tablespoon at a time.
Roll in corn meal and wrap in papers especially for tamales.
Wet papers first so they won't be so stiff.
Put all the tamales in a turkey pan, layering in opposite directions.
Boil about 5 quarts of water and add 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce and 2 ounces chili powder.
Pour over tamales and simmer 2 hours with cover on.
Put the turkey pan across 2 burners on top of stove.
Makes 85 to 100 tamales.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite sizes. Add chopped onions, pecans, grapes and bacon. Mix vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar. Pour over the broccoli mixture and toss well. Refrigerate before serving.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup rice, cold water, salt and butter.
Let come to	a
boil,
then	simmer,
covered, until the water is absorbed.

title: chocolate peanut butter ball
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and peanut butter. Form into balls. Put in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler. Dip balls with toothpick. Place on wax paper to cool.

title: hot and saucy enchiladas
directions: Combine beef
and
onion
in
large skillet; cook until meat is brown, then drain.
Saute tortillas in hot oil briefly to soften; spoon meat mixture evenly in center of each tortilla. Roll up
and
place,
seam
side
down,
in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients,
except Cheddar cheese, in small saucepan. Cook
over
medium
heat
until cheese slices are melted; pour over
enchiladas.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20
to
30 minutes, or bubbly.
Yields 18 enchiladas. Prepare ahead of time; refrigerate until needed.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix 2 to 3 cups flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast; combine milk and water, heat lukewarm, stir into dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add cheese and 1/2 cup flour.
Turn out on floured board, knead smooth, 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and let rise double, covered.
Punch down.
Rest 15 minutes.
Divide in half and roll 14 x 9-inches and roll like jelly roll.
Place seam down, let rise double.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.
Brush with melted butter.

title: cherry delight
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, then mix together with cherry pie filling and sweetened condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip and nuts. Mix all thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat 1/3 cup chips over low heat or in microwave until melted.
Mix melted chocolate, baking mix, nuts, 1/3 cup sugar, milk, oil, vanilla and egg in bowl.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Heat water and 2/3 cup sugar to boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips until melted.
Slowly and evenly pour over mixture in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: delicious beef stew
directions: In 2 quart casserole (glass), mix all the ingredients together.
Bake for 3 hours or more at 225°.
Make sure casserole is covered.
Stir twice during 3 hours.

title: party pizzas
directions: Cook sausage; do not drain off grease.
Add cheese.
(Turn burner to very low.)
Add spices and mix.
Spread on bread.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(You can freeze these before baking.
If frozen, bake 5 minutes longer.)

title: orange beets
directions: Combine cornstarch, ginger, nutmeg and orange juice.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add beets and mandarin oranges. Bring to a boil or until thoroughly heated. Serves 6 people.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Break up cornbread.
Mix everything together, except margarine.
Pour into crock-pot and dot with margarine.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours, 2 hours on high.
Makes 16 servings.

title: callers seafood dinner
directions: Before dance, select favorite brand of sardine; be sure it has a "key opener" so you won't need regular opener.
Open sardines. Use pocket knife to peel and slice onion.
Use same knife to ease out sardines and put on cracker.
Alternate bite of sardine and cracker with onion.
Finish off with moon pie and cola.
Belch about twice and call dance.
(Save cola can for recycling.)
Makes one serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon very crisp; crumble. Fry onion in bacon fat (or other).
Combine all ingredients.
Heat to just below boiling point and remain for a few minutes for flavor.
Reheat to desired temperature and serve.
Serves 6.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Heat oven to 350° and bake the potatoes until done.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Slowly blend in flour with a wire whisk until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add milk to the butter and flour mixture, whisking constantly.
Cut potatoes in half; scoop out the inside and set aside.
Chop half the potato peels and discard the remainder.
When milk mixture is very hot, whisk in the potatoes.
Add onion and potato peels.
Whisk well; add sour cream and crumbled bacon.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese a little at a time until it is melted in.
Serve with crusty French bread and fresh butter.

title: zucchini nibbles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease skillet or spray with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins and currants in saucepan with water to cover until they swell.
Drain and set aside.
Chop all fruit and set aside.
Mix shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Mix in grape juice and mayonnaise.
Combine flour and spices; mix into the batter.
Add vanilla.
Flour fruit and mix in well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: self-crust egg custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add milk, Pet milk and melted butter.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease 9-inch pie pan with butter.
Pour in mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Melt margarine in flat pan or cake pan.
Dip chicken pieces into milk and coat with dry mixture.
Lay pieces in pan; don't crowd! Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Turn pieces over and bake 20 minutes more.
If chicken pieces are large, allow 5 to 10 more minutes.

title: reece's cup pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar together. Pour in graham cracker crust. Pack down. Mix pudding as directed for pie on box. Pour on top. Chill 1 hour.

title: bird seed(edible)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and eat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain, set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and saute 2 minutes.
Add cheese and let melt over low heat.
Add mayonnaise, soup and dry Minute Rice and mix well.
If too dry, add some water.
Add cooked broccoli. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until nice and bubbly.
Remove from oven the last 5 minutes and top with stack of Ritz crackers, crushed and mixed with 1 stick melted butter.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Thickly slice tomatoes (approximately half of medium tomato). Place slices in greased baking dish and cover each slice thickly with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with garlic, basil and salt.
Broil in oven until mayonnaise bubbles.
(Be careful to take them out before mayonnaise turns brown.)

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Note: Add some sliced or chopped pimento for extra color.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs together at high speed for 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour; beat 1 minute on third speed.
Add rest of flour and milk; beat 1 minute on third speed.
Add flavoring and mix.
Bake in 4 layers at 350° until done.

title: banana bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Beat shortening until creamy and glossy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until thick and pale yellow.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas. Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 20 to 30 minutes.

title: reese's pieces
directions: Melt chocolate and pour in a muffin cup cut down halfway.
Let set up for a minute.

title: german slaw
directions: Place alternate layers of cabbage and onions in a large bowl. Cover
with
sugar and sprinkle with celery seed.
Boil together vinegar,
salt
and
mustard.
Add oil and bring to a boil again. Pour
over cabbage and onions; do not mix.	Cover and
refrigerate 24 hours;
stir and serve.	Keeps indefinitely.
Grated carrot could be added for color.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla.
Add egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten crisscross with fork.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: green salad
directions: Drain vegetables and pimentos. Pour liquid mixture over vegetables. Cover and store overnight in refrigerator. Keeps well.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cream of tartar in pot.
Let come to boil.
Add crackers; do not stir!
Set aside and cook for 15 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust; sprinkle with spices and sugar.
Dot with oleo generously.
Put top on pie.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: m.j.m's meat loaf
directions: Crumble crackers and bread in a large bowl.
Add enough milk to soften bread and cracker crumbs, the add beef and all the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a loaf pan or casserole dish. Cover top with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce for grilled chicken
directions: Soak chicken in sauce at least 2 hours before cooking.
For 1 chicken, use this recipe; for 2 chickens, 1 1/2 times.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Salt and lightly pepper pork chops.
Brown chops in shortening and drain off drippings.
Pour a mixture of soup, milk and water over chops.
Add a thinly sliced onion if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir gravy well before serving.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate bits in microwave.
Stir in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil-lined cookie sheets. Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: fruit tart
directions: Cut flour, sugar and margarine with a knife.
Add pecans. Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake exactly 20 minutes at 350°.

title: request green beans for 75
directions: Alternate layers of drained beans and onion. Mix soup, mushrooms with liquids and water chestnuts. Pour over beans and onion. Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: french delight
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip until well blended.
Line 9 x 13-inch cake pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers; line crackers over mixture.
Pour rest of mixture over crackers.
Line crackers over mixture.
Heat icing for 30 seconds.
Pour and smooth over crackers.
Let stand for about 24 hours.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Saute ground chuck and onions until meat loses its pink color and onions are soft.
Drain.
Stir in peas, tomatoes with chilies, mushroom soup, chicken soup and enchilada sauce.

title: corned beef hash casserole
directions: Place layer of hash, layer of vegetables, layer of potatoes. In separate boiler, mix butter, flour and water.
Cook until thick.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 30 minutes).

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: On each piece of chicken, place 1 cheese slice and 1 slice of ham. Roll up and secure with toothpick.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth.
Add shrimp soup with fork until blended.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: taco on a plate
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. In boiler, add stewed tomatoes, kidney beans, beef and taco seasoning.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: pancake puff
directions: Mix flour, eggs, milk and cinnamon together,
leaving butter a bit lumpy.
Melt butter in 9-inch pie plate; pour batter on top of it and bake at 425°
for 20 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Sift powdered sugar on top.
Serve at once with maple syrup.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, salt, egg, butter and orange juice; beat until smooth.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with peanut brittle.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Place cooked chicken, sauteed onion, cooked peas and cooked carrots in a pan.
Cover with chicken broth.
Salt and pepper to your desire.
Thicken with a paste made from plain flour and water.
Serve on toast.

title: baked purple passion
directions: Mix olive oil and spices.
Lightly baste eggplant slices in olive oil spice mixture.
Place on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Flip each eggplant slice and add tomato slices.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese near end of cooking time.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add rice and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream, then add nuts and cherries.
Put in a dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all of the above except the french fried onions.
Pour into a baking dish and cook at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pour french fried onions on top and cook for about 10 minutes more. Serve hot.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy; add lemon juice.
Add the drained crab meat.
Put in ovenproof small casserole.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly.
Serve with assorted crackers. Servings:

title: mocha caramel custard
directions: In a 10-inch heavy skillet, stir 1/2 cup sugar over heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and divide caramel between 6 custard cups, swirling to coat bottoms.
In same skillet, combine milk, 1/4 cup sugar, chocolate, salt and coffee.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs and coffee liqueur.
Pour into custard cups. Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour hot water in pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool, then chill.
To serve, loosen around edges and invert into bowl.
Top with cream.

title: coconut almond milk
directions: Combine almonds and coconut in dry blender.
Whiz until fine. Add
salt,
vanilla
and 1 cup water.
Whiz 1 to 2 minutes.
Add water to desired consistency.
Strain, if desired.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts; set aside.
Combine other ingredients and add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks and cool completely. This will make 5 small loaves in 5 3/4 x 3 x 2 1/8-inch pans.

title: blender dressing
directions: Blend in a blender.
Store in refrigerator in glass jar.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in butter or oil.
Add bread crumbs and tomato sauce.
Set aside.
Wash and cut zucchini into 1/2-inch slices.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, layer zucchini, then meat mixture and half the cheese.
Repeat. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes.

title: phillipino chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone.
Cook macaroni noodles; drain.
Add chicken, macaroni, relish, pineapple, raisins and cubed cheese. Add mayonnaise and sweetened condensed milk.
Mix well and serve. Keep refrigerated.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray/grease casserole. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole.
Bake 1 hour or until firm.
Quick, easy and tasty, especially on a cool day.

title: red rice with chicken sauce
directions: Mix all spices in medium pot.
Put in rice.
After about 15 minutes, rice should be done.
Remove with a spoon.
Clean the chicken and mix with oil and water.
Let it boil.
Cut the potatoes and put in with chicken.
At the end, you will enjoy a beautiful dish.

title: pistachio sour cream bread
directions: In small bowl, toss together the brown sugar, cinnamon and walnuts; set aside.
Grease and flour 4 small (4 x 8-inch) bread tins.
With mixer, beat together cake mix, pudding, sour cream, eggs, oil and water.
Pour half of batter into tins.
Sprinkle half sugar mixture on top, then add remaining batter and over that remaining sugar mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Makes nice coffee cake in Bundt pan.)

title: texas white trash
directions: Melt white chocolate and oil in double boiler on low heat. Mix all ingredients together and pour melted chocolate over them. Stir well and pour out on wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Break apart to serve.

title: crab imperial
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all remaining ingredients except crabmeat. Cook on top of stove until thickened (low flame).
Add crabmeat. Put in shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake until brown. Can be baked in casserole too.

title: no-guilt potato salad
directions: Using a rubber scraper, in a medium bowl combine all ingredients well.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add cut up rhubarb, strawberry Jell-O, sugar and mini marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix. Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange dip for fruit
directions: Blend juice with milk.
Add sour cream and pudding mix.
Chill and use as dip with fruit.

title: wedding punch
directions: Put all of the fruit into a blender and puree.
Mix the sugar and water, place it over a low heat and dissolve.
Mix all of the ingredients well and divide into 5 equal portions in quart freezer bags and freeze.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Then beat butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks.
Beat until well mixed, then add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, lemon and milk.
Last of all fold in egg whites.
Pour in well-greased tube pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: garlic-buttered shrimp
directions: Melt butter; stir in parsley, garlic, hot pepper sauce and salt.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes over medium flame.
Add wine; heat through.
Thread shrimp on skewers.
Grill over flame at high to medium setting for 12 minutes, turning frequently and brushing with butter mixture.
Yields 15 to 18 appetizers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in round layer pan (9 x 1 1/2 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Place pineapple slice in the center, cut remaining in half and arrange with cherries and pecans.
Prepare dinette batter.
Pour evenly over fruit and nuts in pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Invert and serve.

title: potatoes and pennies(casserole)
directions: Combine potatoes and onion.
Sprinkle with flour and season with salt and pepper.
Add milk and hot dogs.
Put in ungreased dish.
Dot with fat or butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cut cherries in half and pineapple in comparable pieces. Separate eggs and set whites aside.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix juice or milk with sugar and flour. Then pour into pan of melted butter.
Put berries on top of batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: lilac pie
directions: Spread coconut on a cookie sheet and bake at 325° until light brown.
Put into bowl and toss with melted butter.
Spread lightly over bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Do not press.
Cool for 1 hour or more in refrigerator.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add one egg at a time, then mix again after each egg.
Add salt and baking powder to flour.
Mix well and add flour mixture and sour cream alternately.
Mix well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Based on 30 servings.
Each serving contains: 155 calories; 5g fat; 76mg sodium; 52mg cholesterol.

title: zucchini honey bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Peel zucchini.
Shred enough to measure 2 cups.
Combine zucchini and the remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just enough until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: italian grilled chicken
directions: Soak thawed chicken breasts in Italian dressing overnight. Grill breasts for 5 to 10 minutes on each side.
Serve with your favorite side dishes.

title: cake balls
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in brown sugar and beat 1 minute.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder together, then add to egg mixture. Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Dump into 9 x 9-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Take a teaspoon of mixture and form into small balls.
Dip balls in granulated sugar.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine other ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: layered chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender and debone.
Cut into small pieces. In bottom of 3-quart casserole, place thin slices of bread.
Cover bread with diced chicken and sprinkle over the hard-cooked eggs. Sprinkle with pimentos and mushrooms.
Pour the milk over this. Place water chestnuts over top.
Cover entire mixture with the cheese slices.
Spread the chicken soup over top.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Before using, take out of refrigerator and allow to reach room temperature.
Remove plastic wrap.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and toast until slightly brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: tuna breyani
directions: Heat oil in frying pan; fry potato slices for about 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan; fry onion until golden.
Add spices and vegetables; cook for 10 more minutes.
Layer 375 ml rice in a large saucepan (or electric skillet).
Top with tuna, potatoes, mixed vegetables, remaining rice and hot water.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes on medium.
Serve garnished with hard-boiled egg.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: meatballs and cheesy shells(recipe can be halved or doubled)
directions: Mix together meat, bread crumbs (moistened with milk), egg, cheese, parsley, garlic and peppers.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls. Brown in heated oil until crisp and cooked.
Don't crowd when browning.
Next, heat tomato sauce and oregano.
Keep warm.
Then cook shells according to package directions.
Drain well.
Spoon a thin coating of sauce in oiled baking dish.
Fill each shell with about 1 tablespoon Ricotta cheese.
Arrange in dish.
Place meatballs among the shells.
Spoon remaining sauce over.
Sprinkle with the cheeses.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir salt pork and onion in Dutch oven until pork is crisp and onion is tender.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Stir clam liquid, potatoes, celery and water into onion and pork.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and boil until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in clams and remaining ingredients.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 servings, 160 calories per serving.

title: stratt-chio-nattis
directions: Remove sausage skin and crumble.
Cook until done.
Drain. Boil pasta in water according to package directions until just done (add a little salt and oil to water).
Rinse and return to large pot.
Cut up into small pieces 1/2 pound of butter or margarine. Add to pasta until melted.
Beat 1 egg and add to pasta mixing lightly but constantly for about 20 seconds until egg coats the pasta.
Add Italian cheese.
Add sausage.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice and milk together and let stand in double boiler under low heat for 2 to 3 hours.
Then cool.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt margarine; add cocoa and mix well.
Add eggs and sugar; mix.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and pecans.
Stir in flour, 1/2 cup at a time, and mix well.
Use spoon to mix.
Do not use electric mixer.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips
1/2-inch
wide.
Place
in a 2 quart casserole.
Cover dish
with lid or vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, stirring twice.
Remove
chicken
from casserole and set aside. Discard juices.

title: snickers style dessert bars(a weight watcher's dessert)
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth.
Put into 8 x 8-inch square pan or 6 custard cups.

title: low country boil
directions: In a large pot, fill halfway with water.
Put in potatoes, peeled onions and cleaned corn.
Cook for 30 minutes over medium heat.
Put green beans on top.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces or use shrimp.
Throw that on top and cover pot.
Cook for about 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Dice chicken meat.
Cook half bag noodles, then drain.
Then add the rest of the ingredients to chicken broth.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown
ground
beef.
Just before brown, chop onion and add to meat.
Stir in soup mix.
Add Veg-All and tomato sauce. Add rice and
enough
water to make soupy.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: my great-grandma's brownies
directions: Cream oleo and add sugar; mix well.
Add eggs and beat well. Add vanilla.
Mix cocoa and flour and add to mixture.
Add pecans. Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish that is greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add butter and cut into dry ingredients to form crumbs.
Remove 3/4 cup crumbs and stir in cinnamon (this will be used as topping).
To remaining crumbs, add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square pan and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shelby's potatoes
directions: Brown sausage.
Saute onions and bell pepper.
Add hash browns.
When potatoes are done, add Mozzarella cheese and jalapeno pepper.
Transfer to serving dish.
Add Cheddar cheese on top.
Cover with foil so cheese will melt.

title: mock angel food cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add gradually scalded milk.
Fold in egg whites (beaten until stiff).
Add vanilla.

title: chicken with rice
directions: In paper bag, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Shake chicken in and brown in oil.
Combine other ingredients in large skillet; mix with chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until done.

title: orange juice shake
directions: Combine ingredients in a blender to desired thickness.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups, 100 calories/cup.
Nutritious during pregnancy (consult your physician).

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with bay leaves.
Cool and grate.
Combine soup, sour cream and milk.
Layer potatoes, onions, cheese and sour cream mixture in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Top with butter and a little cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar, cornstarch and apple juice slowly until thickens.
Let cool.
Chop apples and add to mixture.
Top with Cool Whip with mayonnaise.
Garnish with red and green cherries, grated cheese or chopped nuts.
This will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer noodles, hamburger, cheeses and sauce. Add another layer of each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt together butter and chocolate.
Add alternately the sugar, condensed milk and salt.
Bring to boil in double boiler and add vanilla.

title: savory pheasant crescent squares
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Saute pheasant in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Mix together cream cheese, pheasant, salt, pepper, milk and onion.

title: layer creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, syrup and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: berries on the square
directions: Arrange 9 halves of graham crackers in bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Prepare pudding with 2 cups milk.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Pour half of pudding mix over crackers.
Place fruit on top of pudding.
Arrange remaining 9 halves of graham crackers on top of fruit.
Add remaining pudding mix over crackers.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with whole fruit.
Bananas or canned peaches may be substituted for berries.

title: texas brownies
directions: *If you don't have buttermilk on hand, substitute 2 teaspoons of vinegar or lemon juice mixed with 1/2 cup of milk or use powdered buttermilk according to the package directions.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put sauerkraut in a large bowl.
Add celery, green pepper and onions.
Grate carrots and add them to mixture.
Add sugar and stir with wooden spoon.
Cover tightly and marinate in the refrigerator for 2 or 3 days; stir 2 or 3 times a day (optional). All vegetables become crisp as the salad ages a day or so.
Serves 4.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken breasts flat, or buy chicken tenders.
In olive oil brown onion, add chicken and brown.
The add mushrooms and garlic.
Cook until chicken is about done, then add wine and reduce for 1-2 minutes.

title: coconut crunch pie
directions: Melt margarine and combine all ingredients together. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: olga-type flatbread
directions: In a saucepan, scald milk.
Remove to a large bowl.
Add honey, margarine and salt to milk; stir
until margarine is melted.
Set aside to cool until milk is lukewarm.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Cook turnips in boiling water until tender; drain thoroughly. Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens.
Combine sauce and turnips; pour into a casserole.
Top with cheese; bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° until done. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Add cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Ladle on a hot greasy griddle.

title: ricki's vegetable soup
directions: Saute garlic for 15 minutes.
Add onions, peppers, chicken stock and spinach.
Cook on high for 10 minutes.
Add other vegetables and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Add tomato or V-8 juice, basil and seasoned salt; simmer for 2 hours.

title: spanish caldo gallego
directions: Soak the dried white beans overnight in water.
Drain well.
In an 8-quart stockpot, place 2 1/2 cups water, soaked beans, chicken thighs, chorizo, ham, salt pork, onion, garlic, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer all, covered, for 45 minutes, or until the chicken is tender.
Remove the chicken from the pot. Debone the chicken.
Chop the meat and reserve.

title: bruna boner(swedish brown beans)
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Cook slowly in same water until tender (about 2 hours).
Add salt, molasses, vinegar and sugar.
If they seem too juicy, thicken with a little cornstarch paste.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, vanilla, flour and salt.
Blend until moist.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread chocolate while warm. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine the last 4 items with broccoli.
Melt margarine and mix with Pepperidge Farm and cover casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: marble cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour 3/4 of the batter into a well-greased spring-form pan.
Pour 3/4 cup Hershey's chocolate syrup into the remaining batter and mix.
Pour this mixture over cake mix in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and add baking powder and salt.
Sift three times.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not peek!

title: sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix dry ingredients together; stir into yeast.
Cut in shortening.
Roll dough out onto floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: pay day bars
directions: Melt peanut butter, Karo syrup and sugar on stove. Put chips in 9 x 13 pan. Pour mixture over top and let cool.

title: strawberry salad with pretzels
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add strawberries and put in refrigerator to thicken.
Break pretzels.
Mix brown sugar and margarine, then add pretzels.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish; pack to bottom.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled pretzels and top with fruit mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.
This can be used as a salad or dessert.
You can substitute raspberry Jell-O and raspberries or peach or any other fruit combination.

title: cheddar puffs
directions: Mix together and spoon onto English muffins. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Quarter the muffins. Serve immediately.

title: maggie's lemonade
directions: If you are using fresh lemons, squeeze the juice from enough lemons to make 1 cup juice.
Mix sugar, lemon juice and water in a large pitcher.
Add cherry juice if you want to make your lemonade pink.
Pour the lemonade over ice cubes in tall glasses.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dried bean chili(serves 10)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Cover with water and simmer for 2 hours, checking the fluid level periodically.
Cook ground beef. Add beef and spices.
Continue to cook for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Preparation Time:
30 minutes.

title: rotel chicken(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Cook noodles in broth until tender; drain. Saute butter, onions and bell pepper; add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Add remaining ingredients. Stir in large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients into large container.
Store tightly covered.
For each serving, mix 1/4 cup boiling hot water into cup.

title: cranberry-barbecued chicken wings
directions: Place chicken in shallow glass dish.
Prepare Cranberry Marinade.
Pour marinade over chicken; turn to coat with marinade. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: In the bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish (greased), place croutons.
Combine in large bowl eggs, milk,
cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix until blended.
Pour about 1/2 inch of egg mixture over croutons and let sit for about 5 minutes (just to let croutons soften a bit).
Pour rest of egg mixture over croutons. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares and serve hot with toast, muffins, etc.
So easy to make and convenient for company.
Just prepare and cook the night before.
Cool and refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature and reheat the next day!

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Add oil. Sift dry ingredients into egg mixture. Add pumpkin, blending well. Bake in tube pan or 9x13in. pan at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 mins.

title: chewy chocolate brownies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter.
Add flour, cocoa and salt, stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Better to underbake to keep them chewy.
These may be iced with chocolate icing or served with ice cream.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and lay in casserole dish. Saute bell pepper, onion and mushrooms in margarine. Add Ro-Tel and cut up cheese. After mixture melts, pour over potatoes. Heat in oven until mixture bubbles at 350°.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water, just until tender.
Put in crock-pot and add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Cook meat.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Put in a glass pie plate.
Heat in microwave until bubbly.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar, Karo and water together and boil slowly until it forms a soft ball (235°) on candy thermometer.
Add salt and peanuts; stir mixture until it becomes a light yellow (290°) on thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and soda.
Mixture will bubble.
Beat until butter is melted and mixture begins to thicken.
Pour on greased platters and cool partially by lifting around edges with spatula.
When firm, but still warm, turn over. Break in pieces when cold.

title: coconut cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pan with paper liners.
In bowl, mix flour, cornstarch, baking powder, lemon rind and lemon extract together.
Stir in honey.
Stir in egg and 1 1/4 cups coconut.

title: "quickie" garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to broil.
In a large bowl, combine cheeses, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Spread mixture on bread and broil for a few minutes (3 to 4), until cheese top is golden brown and bubbly.
Slice and serve immediately.

title: simple hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a casserole dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tangy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.

title: sweet vidalia onion pie
directions: Cook onions, sliced, about 15 minutes in small amount of oil or margarine, enough to fill pie shell.
Mix eggs and milk; season to taste.
Pour over onions.
Cover with shredded cheese. Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, crushed pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
Shape into ball; roll into remaining nuts.
Wrap in foil.
To serve, place on serving plate, using kale for greenery.
Arrange slices of pineapple and cherries.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Refrigerate.
Reshape and can be used several times.

title: buttered caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in large mixing bowl.
Bring to boil, everything except vanilla and soda.
Simmer 5 minutes while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add the vanilla and soda.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add liquids with 3/4 cup flat beer. Roll ice cream balls in crushed corn flakes.
Freeze overnight. Dip into mixture.
Then dip in egg whites (not too stiff), covering ice cream thoroughly.
Deep fry; drain on paper towels.

title: eggs & sausage casserole(a low carb recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Lightly coat a 1-1/2 quart baking dish with non stick vegetable spray and set aside.
Combine sour cream, salt, paprika and mustard in a small bowl and blend well.
Spread half the cheddar cheese on bottom of the prepared baking dish.
Spoon dollops of half the sour cream mixture over the cheese.
Distribute all the sausage over the sour cream and pour the beaten eggs over the sausage.
Spoon dollops of remaining sour cream over the edges and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until the eggs are set.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening. Beat thoroughly.
Grease pan, 8 or 9-inch square.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-qt. casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas taters
directions: Add all the ingredients together with hash browns added last. Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes or 2 cups potato chips, crushed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; work in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Form in small balls.
Place
on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: cheesy biscuits
directions: Combine
flour,
baking
powder,
baking soda and salt. Cut butter into flour until mixture develops texture of coarse meal or sand.
Stir
cheese
into mixture until coated.
Pour milk a little
at	a
time until moist and holds together.
Do not overmix.
Roll
biscuits
to
1/2-inch thickness.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.

title: barley chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water to cover.
Bone and cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Reserve broth for later use.
Brown barley in butter or margarine.
Add French onion soup and sliced mushrooms.
Cover and cook on stove top at low heat until barley has absorbed liquid (about 30 minutes for quick-cooking barley; longer for regular barley).

title: celery and mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Stir-fry mushrooms.
Add celery, sugar and soy sauce.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until celery becomes bright green.
Serve hot.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix soups and milk together. Layer peas, soup mixture and then crackers.
Repeat.
Cook at 375° for 20 minutes or microwave 5 minutes.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add potatoes; cover and cook slowly, 10 minutes, turning.
Add 1/2 of salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish (1 1/2 quart).
Melt oleo, add onions and beef; cook until browned.
Add remaining salt and pepper.
Put on top of potatoes. Cover with sauce.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° .

title: turkey sausage and tortellini salad
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add turkey sausage; brown 8 to 10 minutes, turning occasionally.
Reduce heat to low; cover and continue cooking sausage 8 to 10 minutes more, turning once.
When cool, cut sausage into 1/4-inch slices.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan, Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over dough, bake at 350.
Can be frozen.

title: homemade chicken soup
directions: Add chicken (cooked) back into same broth; add all ingredients except noodles and sausage.
Simmer 1 hour.
In skillet and water, simmer down sausage that has been cut into circles, then in fourths.
When vegetables are tender, add noodles; simmer 15 minutes or so.

title: squash-tomato casserole
directions: In a baking dish, melt butter.
Make layers of squash, onion and tomatoes.
Cover and cook in a moderate 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Just before serving, uncover and top with cheese; heat until cheese melts.

title: john y. brown pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes depending on your oven.
I turn mine down so it will not be too brown or you can cover with foil after it has baked for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat until light.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole dish in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.
Serves 8.

title: collard greens with ham hocks
directions: Wash ham hocks and cook in pressure cooker for 45 minutes. Let pot cool before opening.
Meanwhile, clean collards and cut them up.
Wash collards until clean (no sand can be felt in bottom of sink).
Put bacon grease in pot and heat it.

Add the collards, pepper and liquid from the ham hocks along with the cut up ham hocks and cook over moderate heat approximately 30 minutes to an hour if the collards are tender, or until they reach the tenderness you desire.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients with a whisk.
Preheat large frying pan or griddle to 425°.
Makes 12 four-inch pancakes.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Cut each into 2 parts. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Combine remaining ingredients. Place wings in pan. Pour sauce over and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water; cook until clear.
Remove from
heat, add a few drops of red food coloring and strawberry gelatin; stir well. Line shell with whole strawberries.
Fill shell with cooked mixture.
Place in refrigerator until quite thick.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Simmer zucchini (cut in 1/2 inch slices) in salted water to cover until tender, usually about 10 minutes. Drain.
Saute onion in margarine; add sour cream and cheese. Season zucchini with salt and a little pepper.
Mix with onion sauce.
Layer in baking dish with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake about 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: ice cream layer cake
directions: Cut cake lengthwise into 3 layers.
Spread ice cream between layers.
Place cake in freezer to harden.
Whip cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Use to frost top and sides of cake.
Cover with coconut; return to freezer until whipped cream is hard.
Wrap in freezer paper; freeze.

title: lemon lime cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Punch holes in cake and allow to cool.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water. Add cold water.
Pour jello into cake holes.
Blend together Cool Whip and lemon pudding mix, make sure it is mixed well or your icing will be sour tasting.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
This makes a great summer cake because it stays cold.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy kettle over low heat.
Mix sugar, salt and flour; add to melted butter, stirring until mixture is heated. Add the milk and cook over medium heat.
When the mixture begins to thicken, add the beaten egg yolks.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Cool slightly and add vanilla before pouring into a baked pie shell.
Add meringue, if desired.
I use filled soybean milk (8 ounce can).

title: northern lights punch
directions: Place frozen daiquiri mix and pineapple juice in punch bowl and let thaw enough to blend together.
Add green coloring just before serving.
Gently add ice cold Sprite and 7-Up.
Makes 35 punch cup servings.

title: date bars
directions: Beat egg yolks until light. Add sugar. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add chopped dates and nuts to flour, mixing well so as to separate them.
Add to eggs and sugar the vanilla and salt. Beat egg whites stiff.
Mix flour mixture and egg mixture together. Fold in egg whites. Cook in a greased 6 x 12-inch pan at 300° until done. Cut in 1 x 4-inch strips while still hot and roll in powdered sugar.

title: sweet 'n sour pork
directions: Brown pork strips in hot oil in large skillet.
Add onion pieces and water.
Cover and simmer approximately 20 minutes. Meanwhile, drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, ginger and salt.
Blend in juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Add this to pork along with green pepper (if using green pepper).
Stir just until thickened and starts to bubble.
Add pineapple chunks to mixture.
Mix, by stirring.
Serves 4 over fried rice.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Mix and cream together sugar, egg, fruit cocktail with juice, baking soda, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into greased 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts together.
Sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix ground chuck, carrots, green beans, zucchini, salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Wrap about 3 tablespoons mixture into each wrap.

title: sweet-and-sour meatballs
directions: Cook meatballs in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat 4 minutes or until browned. Drain meatballs and return to skillet. Add chili sauce and jelly and cook until jelly melts, stirring constantly. Add pineapple, if desired. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring mixture occasionally.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add orange juice, flour (measure after sifted), baking powder and vanilla.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in batter.
Cover top with cherry pie filling; cut in slightly.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven. Dust top with confectioners sugar when removed from oven.
Serves 12.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Mix spinach, onion, celery and cottage cheese.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into a greased mold and refrigerate.

title: fruit whip
directions: Take chilled milk and put in chilled bowl to whip until thick like whipped cream.
Then add lemon juice and salt and whip again to thicken.
Add fruit puree and sugar to taste for sweetening. Whip briefly to mix and serve immediately.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Add onions, peppers, creamed corn and cheese.
Mix cornmeal, milk, eggs and oil.
Pour half in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, then pour in the meat mixture. Then add the rest of the corn bread mixture.
Bake for 1 hour in 400° oven.

title: school house chili
directions: Fry hamburger a while before adding other ingredients, then cook slowly for about 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: marie linville's diet pineapple bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 1 hour in loaf or tube pan at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Brown hamburger, sausages, pepper and onion; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce; melt cream cheese into mixture.
Layer noodles, sauce and remaining cheeses.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spice cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Add eggs and bake in 350° oven until done.

title: stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large container and simmer until done.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until almost tender; drain and place in casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients in a saucepan and cook until smooth.
Pour over cabbage; top with buttered cracker crumbs and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Let cool.
Break candy bars into tiny pieces.
Prepare the pudding with milk; beat with mixer.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Let stand overnight or all day.
Boil 10-12 minutes add 1 box 3 oz jello seal hot.

title: three minute microwave fudge
directions: Stir all ingredients, except the butter, together in a glass bowl.
Put the butter on top; microwave on Roast for 3 minutes (or High for 2 minutes).
Stir until smooth.
Blend in the nuts.
Pour into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill.

title: kahlua velvet frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Blend until smooth.
Yield:
About 6 servings.

title: japanese steak
directions: Cut steak into small strips and marinate
in soy sauce 3 hours or overnight.
Saute onions, green peppers and celery in vegetable oil.
Drain steak; save soy sauce.
Brown steak in vegetable oil; add onions, peppers, celery and soy sauce.
Cook slowly, covered, for 45 minutes, or until steak is tender.
Drain and rinse Chinese vegetables.
Add to steak along with drained, sliced mushrooms and zucchini.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add almonds and serve over rice.
Season to taste.

title: stuffed pepper casserole
directions: Put green peppers, onion and ground beef in a skillet.
Cook until ground beef is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add undrained tomatoes or tomato sauce, uncooked rice, water, salt, Worcestershire sauce and a dash of pepper. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 18 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in 1/2 of the cheese. Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: poppy (seed) cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add poppy filling.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and sour cream. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add gradually to poppy filling mixture, beating well after each addition.
Fold in STIFFLY beaten egg whites.
Pour into a greased 9 or 10-inch tube pan which has the bottom lined with wax paper.
Bake about 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until well done.
Allow cake to cool about 5 minutes; remove from pan and peel off wax paper.
Decorate top of cake by sifting confectioners sugar through a paper doily or a cut out.

title: meat balls with gravy
directions: Chop onion, celery and green pepper very fine, or grind.
Mash garlic in press.
Combine all ingredients, except Wesson oil and bouillon cubes.
Form into desired size meat balls.
Roll in flour and brown in hot Wesson oil over medium heat.
As they brown, remove and set aside until all are brown.
Pour 2 cups water into pan drippings.
Add the bouillon cubes and place meat balls back into pot.
Cover; let simmer slowly for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10, depending on size of meat balls.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Add Jell-O to hot water; dissolve and add marshmallows.
Cool; refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Beat until light green in color.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Whip the cream, then add to mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: broccoli and tomato salad
directions: Cut broccoli, tomato and onions. Combine in a bowl. Mix remaining ingredients and add to broccoli. Refrigerate overnight if possible. Stir as often as possible.

title: rice
directions: When the bubbles come up, stir it.
Put in your rice.
After it's cooked, you can put in butter, or you can eat it without butter.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar and place in a large mixing bowl.
Put butter, cocoa, Coke and marshmallows into a small boiler.
Simmer until marshmallows are melted.
Take off of burner and let it cool off slightly.
Add melted mixture to flour and sugar and blend well.
Blend in 2 well beaten eggs.
Add buttermilk with baking soda in it.
Pour in greased and floured pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour icing on cake while warm.

title: mocha-oatmeal cake
directions: Combine instant coffee, quick oats and boiling water; set aside and allow to cool.
Cream oleo and brown sugar in mixer; add vanilla and eggs, combine flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Stir in by hand.
Add coffee and oats mixture and stir together.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Oven temperature is 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: 2 wheat loaves
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add salt, shortening and honey; stir until dissolved.
Add wheat flour and enough white flour to make a soft dough.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Pat sausage into flat rectangle, about 8 x 12-inch.
Partially freeze.
Make Bisquick dough according to directions on box.
Roll out same size as sausage.
Place sausage on dough.
Roll up jellyroll style.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until light brown.
I make these and freeze.
Then slightly and slice to bake.

title: ginger ale cake
directions: Mix and cook 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes three 8-inch layers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
