Generously grease two 9-inch cake pans. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together; set aside. Combine eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla and mix well. Add flour mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts. Stir well. Pour into prepared pans. Bake 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Cool completely.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease skillet and preheat.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix corn meal, eggs, milk and corn.
Sprinkle corn in hot skillet. Pour 1/2 of batter in skillet.
Add onion, cheese, meat and peppers.
Pour remainder on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook until boiling raisins and water.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add sugar, flour, 2 teaspoons lemon juice and margarine.
Then add 3 more tablespoons lemon juice.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange-tapioca salad
directions: Mix tapioca pudding mix and jello mix in a saucepan.
Add boiling water, stirring until jello is dissolved.
Boil until clear, stirring.
Cool.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple. Prepare Dream Whip as directed and fold into mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage in boiling water until wilted, not soft.
Mix meat with other ingredients, reserving 1/3 of tomatoes.
Place equal amounts of meat mixture in each cabbage leaf.
Fold leaves around meat to form rolls.
Pour remaining tomatoes over cabbage rolls.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: bowtie pasta
directions: Brown ground beef and drain, add 2 or 3 cans diced tomatoes, sliced green pepper, sliced onion, mushrooms, clove of garlic, black olives, and sliced sausage.
Add seasoning salt, Cavender's Greek Seasoning, 3-4 dashes of Worcestershire Sauce, 3-4 dashes of hot sauce; all to cooks desire.
Simmer until all onions and peppers are done, then add box of cooked bowtie pasta.
Serve with shredded cheddar cheese, parmesan cheese, and garlic bread.
You can substitute the sliced sausage with ground sausage, or add both and also can add any left over chicken you may have.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown hamburger in iron skillet.
Add ingredients, except noodles and cheese, and cook very slow (the longer the better). Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add to sauce.
Add in cheese.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Cook vegetables and keep warm.
Boil chicken breasts until done, approximately 10 minutes.
Cut into cubes.
Mix all ingredients in a baking dish and warm in oven at 350° or microwave.
Serve over rice, toast or muffins.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, sugar and undissolved yeast.
In a large bowl, mix milk and margarine; heat to warm.
Gradually add to dry ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1 1/2 cups starter and 1 cup flour to make stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured board; knead until smooth, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until double.
Punch down.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.
Let rise until double in loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: maureen's bean dip
directions: Mix all together, then add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Enjoy with tortilla chips!

title: chili hamburger(make and freeze for later)
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients. Shape into 4 hamburg patties. Freeze in a large freezer bag with waxed paper between each one. Grill or fry patties when needed.
Serve on warm hamburger buns.

title: lo-cal blueberry jam
directions: In a saucepan, mash blueberries.
Stir in pectin and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from the heat; stir in the sweetener.
Stir for two minutes.
Spoon into jars. Cool.
Cover, seal and refrigerate.
Yields 1 1/2 pints. Calories:
9 per tablespoon.

title: gudgy's spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
When about done, add rice and saute slightly.
Add other ingredients and simmer covered for 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sauerkraut and vegetables.
Combine other ingredients and pour over sauerkraut mixture.
Stir until all vegetables are coated.
Chill before serving.
Keep in refrigerator; it improves with age.
Especially good served with pinto beans and cornbread.

title: garden ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in a small amount of boiling, unsalted water until crisp-tender; drain and set aside.

title: barbecue bean casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef in a frying pan.
Drain off the excess fat.
Pour this in a large casserole dish.
Pour the large can of pork and beans over ground beef.
Chop onion very fine and pour over this.
Lay slices of cheese on top until covered.
The last step is to place biscuits one at a time on top of this.
Bake in 350° oven until biscuits are done and golden brown.
This is good served with a salad.

title: easy as punch
directions: Reconstitute orange juice according to directions.
Prepare cherry and orange Kool-Aid according to package directions. Combine orange juice, pineapple juice and cherry and orange Kool-Aid in punch bowl; stir in sugar.
Place bananas in blender container.
Process to puree.
Stir into punch just before serving.
Yield: 40 to 50 servings.

title: the all american dessert
directions: Stir 2 cups boiling water into each flavor of Jell-O until dissolved.
Stir 1 cup cold water into each.
Pour into separate 13 x 9-inch pans.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Layer Jell-O, Cool Whip, cake and strawberries in a 3-quart serving dish.

title: custard cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Then mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: diet coke jello salad
directions: Drain fruits and add water to drained juice to equal 1 3/4 cup liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve jello in liquid slowly. Slowly add Coke (it will bubble up).
Add cherries and pineapple. Pour into dish and chill until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Put bacon fat in skillet; add beef, 1/2 cup onions and the garlic and saut, breaking up meat with fork, until onions are limp. Add consomm and wine and bring to a boil. Simmer 1 minute, then add next 5 ingredients and mix well. Add salt to taste and pour into casserole baking dish (9 x 13). Poke tortilla pieces into meat mixture and bake, uncovered, in preheated oven, 350°, for about 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese. Then top with remaining green onion, lettuce, avocado and tomato. Serve at once. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces. Line casserole dish with Doritos chips.
Cover with chicken.
Mix next 6 ingredients together and pour over chicken and chips.
Top with chopped cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
More cheese may be added, if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese over double
boiler; add all other ingredients and beat until well blended.

title: cheese spread
directions: Add the pineapple juice to the olive pimento spread and Cheddar spread. Chill.

title: party mints
directions: Combine ingredients with a few drops of water to make a stiff dough.
Work in food coloring as desired.
Mold in rubber molds.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Cook and cube potatoes.
Combine mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salt, pepper, onions and green pepper.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts, salt and Karo syrup and place in microwavable dish.
Cook 4 minutes on High in microwave.
Stir and rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cook another 4 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in baking soda and pour into greased cookie sheet.
When mixture cools and hardens, it may be broken into pieces of desired size.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef and add onion.
Drain well and discard grease.
In large pot, combine ground beef, onion and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain beans; add mushrooms, onion and tomatoes.
Pour dressing over and allow to marinate.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Store in freezer bags in deep freeze.
Eat as desired.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onion and salt and let stand overnight. Rinse with cold water; drain and squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Add peppers. Mix remaining ingredients in a large kettle and simmer 10 minutes. Add the zucchini mixture and boil 10 minutes more. Seal in sterilized jars. Makes 7 to 8 pints.

title: "pitts stop" blueberry or fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk in medium bowl. Break up butter into small pieces and add to flour mixture.
Drop flour mixture on top of fruit or berries in 1 1/2-quart baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or golden brown.

title: mock whipped cream icing
directions: Beat with mixer on whip for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Boil together rapidly for 5 minutes.

title: barbecued burger beans
directions: Cook lima beans according instructions.
Drain.
In 4-quart casserole, combine lima beans, baked beans and kidney beans.
Stir in 1/4 cup brown sugar, 2 tablespoons salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and prepared mustard.
Mix well and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion with
seasoning in fryer.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour soup over
this
and top with Tater Tots. Cook at 350° until brown or 30 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Dissolve baking soda in the boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll thin.
Cut dough with a cookie cutter. Bake at 325° until light brown.
Watch carefully as cookies brown quickly.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Cover and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serve over pasta.
May use as a pizza sauce also.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Cool.

title: chicken and rice over biscuits
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Cook chicken until white on both sides. Add salt, pepper and poultry seasonings to taste.
Slowly pour in chicken broth.
Cover and cook on simmer for 30 minutes.
Add gravy.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Make rice and biscuits.
Place biscuits on plate.
Pour rice, chunks of chicken and gravy over top of biscuits.

title: foolproof pastry
directions: Mix the flour, Crisco, salt and sugar with a fork until crumbly.
Mix
the	water, lemon juice or vinegar and egg in a small bowl;
add to the crumb mixture.
Mix until dough sticks together.
Refrigerate
for
to
20 minutes.
This makes a double crust or 4 single crust pies.

title: jiffy squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and chopped onion.
Drain and return to pan.
Add eggs and butter.
Layer squash with cheese (2 layers of each, use plenty of cheese).
Crumble bread on top and pat with butter. Bake at 450° until brown on top.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
You can use a different flavor Kool-Aid each time you make the dough.
It's fun to experiment!

title: fruit dip
directions: Warm the cream cheese until soft.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallow cream; mix well.
Add a few drops of food coloring and stir until uniformly colored.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken a la can can
directions: Combine soups, stock and chicken.
Add uncooked rice.
Stir to mix.
Bake in casserole at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: orange bread
directions: Combine orange peel, sugar and water; boil and then simmer for 10 to 15 minutes to make a thin syrup.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg to mixture and enough water to make 2 cups of liquid. Add shortening; then add to flour mixture.
Mix well and then pour into a greased, floured 9 x 9-inch or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carol's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat together the butter, the granulated sugar and the light brown sugar with an electric mixer until light and creamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in the vanilla and the eggs until smooth.

title: sangria blanco
directions: Heat sugar, water and cinnamon to boiling in 1-quart saucepan. Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours, but no longer than 1 week.
Remove cinnamon sticks.

title: double divinity
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/3 cup of water and cook until small amount of syrup forms soft ball in cold water (240°).
Cook remaining 1 1/2 cups of sugar, 1/3 cup of water and corn syrup until it forms a hard ball in cold water (254°).
Cool first syrup slightly.
Add slowly to egg whites, beating constantly about 1 to 2 minutes or until mixture loses its gloss.
Add second syrup in same way.
Add vanilla and turn into greased pan.
Cut in squares when cold.
This candy is softer and creamier than the regular Divinity.
Approximate yield:
about 40 pieces.

title: arkansas smashed potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes before starting.
Dice in large chunks. Put salt into 3 cups of water and bring to a constant boil.
Add prepared potatoes to water.
Let boil for 15 minutes, then drain water.
Add 1/4 cup of water, milk, margarine and black pepper. Begin to cream potatoes while cooking on low temperature until all lumps are mashed out.
Turn off heat.
Season to desired flavor. Serves 3 to 5.

title: bean salad
directions: Stir sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved. Add Wesson oil and other ingredients.
Let stand overnight.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5
minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer wafers, bananas and mixture ending with pudding mixture.
Garnish with wafers.
Chill and serve.

title: mrs. stephenson's plain pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and margarine with sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating continuously.
Add flour and milk, alternating (add 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup milk, 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup milk and last cup of flour with baking powder).
Add flavorings.
Bake in a 10-inch angel food pan for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes, or until cake tests done, at 325°.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes (cut in cubes) until tender.
Drain.
Heat butter in skillet and saute onion.
Blend in flour, paprika and salt.
Heat until mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add bouillon stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
While beating with a whisk, add small amounts of sour cream and paste mixture. Gently mix potatoes into sauce and cook over low heat, turning constantly, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix tomatoes with sugar, black pepper and bread that is broken in small pieces.
Pour into baking dish.
Chip margarine on top. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer dish or bowl with bananas and wafers, alternating each layer.
Combine milk, water, sugar, vanilla, eggs and flour.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour over layers.

title: squash rolls
directions: Put the warm water and sugar into the large bowl of electric mixer.
Sprinkle yeast into this and allow to stand 5 minutes. Add oil, salt, squash and dry milk.
Beat well at low speed. Gradually beat in 2 cups of flour.
Scrape beaters and add the rest of the flour by hand, mixing well.
Let rise 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Let yeast dissolve.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat well and add egg and oil.
Mix well.
Add the rest of the flour until smooth.
Cover and keep in refrigerator.
Punch down if it raises.

title: twice cooked divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Insert thermometer in pan. Stirring constantly, on high, heat until it comes to a boil.
Do not stir again.
Cook to 242°.
Remove from heat and drizzle 1/3 into egg whites, beating constantly.
Return syrup to heat and cook to 265°.
Drizzle into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Beat until it begins to lose its gloss and will stand up when dropped by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: pecan 'n' raisin rice
directions: To boiling water, add chicken flavored broth; turn down to simmer, covered, until ready to use.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Cool Whip.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill well.

title: nutty vegetable pilaf
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add broccoli, carrots and onion.
Cook and stir 5 to 7 minutes or until broccoli and carrots are tender and onion is beginning to brown. Add mushrooms, garlic, thyme, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Add rice and pecans; cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring, until well blended and thoroughly heated.
Just before serving sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well and put into 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 325°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: garlic cheese dip
directions: Blend cheese, sour cream, garlic, parsley and seasoning. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: creamy rice fudge
directions: Microwave Instruction:
Combine chocolate morsels, peanut butter and butter in large bowl; cook uncovered on High 1 1/2 minutes or until butter melts and morsels are soft and glossy, but still retain their shape.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and cook on High 45 to 60 seconds or until marshmallows are slightly melted.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in cereal and vanilla until well blended.
Transfer mixture into butter 8-inch pan; spread evenly.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: jocelyn's special pie
directions: About 3 1/2 hours before serving or early in day:
Preheat oven at 350°.
In a heavy small saucepan over low heat, heat chocolate, stirring occasionally, until melted and smooth.
Remove chocolate from heat; cool slightly.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, sugar, melted chocolate and 1 cup corn syrup until smooth.
Stir in peanuts. Pour peanut mixture into frozen pie shell.
Bake pie 60 to 65 minutes, until a knife inserted one inch from edge of pie comes out clean.
Cool pie on wire rack completely.
Brush top of pie with 1 tablespoon corn syrup for attractive sheen.
Makes 12 servings. Each serving:
about 425 calories, 23 g. fat, 53 mg. cholesterol and 215 mg. sodium.

title: parmesan twists
directions: Cream butter; gradually add cheese and sour cream, mixing well.
Combine flour and Italian seasoning.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, blending until smooth.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; divide in half.
Roll out half of dough to a 12x7 inch rectangle, and cut into 6x1/2 inch strips.
Twist each strip 2 or 3 time, and place on a greased cookie sheet. Repeat procedure with the remaining dough.
Combine egg yolk with water.
Brush strips with egg mixture; sprinkle with caraway seeds or poppy seeds.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Yield: about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: country rice pudding
directions: Simmer milk, rice and raisins together in a saucepan until rice is tender.
Beat eggs in a bowl until they are foamy.
Slowly add the milk to the mixture and the sugar to the eggs and stir. Add the vanilla and salt.
Return custard mixture to the saucepan and cook over low heat.
Pour into a serving bowl.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: easy dessert snacks
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and walnuts.
Mix and spread on crackers. Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry fruit delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and Jell-O together.
Drain fruit cocktail.
Pour and mix with pecans.
Mix all together and chill for 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake claire
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon; add nuts.
Set aside.
Mix on medium speed the cake mix, pudding, eggs, melted margarine and sour cream until fairly fluffy.
Spread half of cake batter on ungreased tube (angel food) cake pan.
Sprinkle half of cinnamon, sugar and nut mixture on top.
Then spread remainder of batter over this. Finally sprinkle remainder of sugar mixture on top.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°.
Cover with foil last 15 minutes if nuts are too brown.
Cool on rack at least 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves; garnish with pimento strips.

title: squash casserole
directions: In skillet on medium heat, pour in vegetable oil.
Add squash and onion, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Stir in molasses.
Blend flour with other ingredients, then add molasses mixture and applesauce, beating thoroughly.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in greased square cake pan at 350° for approximately 55 minutes. Ice with chocolate or caramel frosting.

title: alabama way-chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Let cool and then shred it up. Mix chicken, sour cream and soup up in bowl. When it's thoroughly mixed, place in pan, 9 x 9-inch. Crumble crackers on top. Melt butter. Pour on top. Heat oven to 350°. Cook for 30 minutes. Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes, then serve and enjoy.

title: savory cheese biscuits
directions: Add cheese and celery salt to biscuit mix before adding liquid.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick and cut into squares with a floured knife.
Bake as directed on package.

title: no-bake chocolate cookie cheesecake
directions: Prepare crust
according
to package directions.
Soften gelatin
in
water;
stir over low heat until dissolved.
Cool. Gradually add gelatin to cheesecake mix, mixing at medium speed on electric
mixer
until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream and cookies; pour over crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped cream and cookies, if desired.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil until it smokes.
Add onion, pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook over medium heats until veggies are limp, but do not brown.
Stir in water, tomatoes, salt, pepper, cornstarch, shrimp and bay leaves.
Reduce and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple squares
directions: Butter a square cake pan.
Mix ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: provincetown clam pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a deep pie shell.
Cover with upper crust and pierce top crust with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with a pitcher of smooth, creamy white sauce.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil Eagle Brand milk (in cans) in large pan of water for 3 hours.
Let the cans cool completely before opening.
When cool, open cans and stir with a knife.
The Eagle Brand milk will be caramelized.
Pour the caramel into the baked pie shells and chill.
Before serving, spread Cool Whip over the top of the pies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and soda mixture with sour cream.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake in slow oven to start, then moderate.

title: black walnut or coconut cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo well; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well until mixture is creamy.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla, then add nuts or coconut and beat well.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans, well-greased and floured, 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
I use 325°
until golden brown, then turn to 350°.

title: mandie's granola bars
directions: Mix all together.
Press into 2 cookie sheets (I grease mine). Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: chicken fillmore
directions: Pound cutlets until thin.
In a large skillet, saute chicken in melted butter; set aside.
Wash and slice mushrooms; saute in small frying pan until golden.
Set aside.
Cook artichoke hearts in covered saucepan and set aside.
In large skillet, combine all ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low flame for 20 minutes. Serve with chilled dry Italian white wine like Pinot Grigiot or Gavi.

title: cranberry-orange-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
With pastry blender, mix in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in orange peel, orange juice and egg, just until flour is moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.
With spatula, loosen edges of loaf and cool on wire rack.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add margarine, eggs and nuts.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm, about 45 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: throat soother
directions: Dissolve honey in water.
Add vinegar.
Good for sore throat due to coughing, due to colds, etc.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium saucepan, heat pie filling. Pour into ovenproof dish.
Roll biscuits in melted butter, then in brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Place on top of pie filling.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in roaster.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: dirt
directions: Crush Oreos finely.
Let cream cheese and margarine soften.

title: aunt hazel's brownies
directions: Mix and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cut-out cookie dough
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and milk; beat until fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and blend.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out dough and cut out cookies.
Decorate and bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip, sour cream, marshmallows, cherries, nuts, sugar, dates, oranges and any other fruit you wish to use.
Pour into ice cube tray lined with wax paper.
Freeze.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef until meat is browned. Drain off the fat.
Stir in peas, soup, 1/4 cup water, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: my meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef and sausage; mix thoroughly with hand. Add pickles, onion and peppers, mixing well.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; mix and form into loaf. Place in pan.
Brush top of loaf with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix lemon juice with Eagle Brand milk until thick.
Add vanilla, then add the Cool Whip.
Line pie pan with graham cracker crumbs mixed with the oleo, melted.
Cool in refrigerator and pour the milk mixture on top, then pour a can of cherry or blueberry pie filling on and cool and serve.
Good.

title: jan's pralined pecans
directions: Place pecans in large bowl.
Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Pour over nuts and mix with hands.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon and add to nuts, tossing to coat pecans.
Spread pecans on buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and sugar in mixer bowl.
Mix well. Stir in buttermilk and oil.
Pour into lightly greased loaf pans. Bake for 45 minutes or until bread tests done.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Serve warm or cold.

title: my sister-in-law's easy chicken
directions: Slice breasts horizontally to have 8 pieces of fillet.
In oil, slowly brown chicken until no longer pink.
Set aside.
Slice pepper and onions, 1/4-inch widths.
Add soup, pepper, onion and water to chicken.
Return to medium heat and stir constantly until peppers and onions are the way you like them.
Serve immediately. Serve with your own side dishes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water. Add strawberries and pineapple, juice and bananas. Pour 1/2 mixture into 8x8 pan. Chill till firm. Spread 1 cup sour cream. Pour remaining jello mixture on top. Chill till firm. Top with sour cream.

title: dried beef rolls
directions: Soften the cream cheese and mix in horseradish thoroughly. Spread cheese mixture very thin over a slice of meat.
Roll up and cut in 1 1/2-inch pieces and stick with toothpicks.
Chill before serving.

title: lentil soup with dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: cookie press sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour gradually; cream well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Force through cookie press into desired shapes onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with colored sugars, chocolate chips or colored candies before baking.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: crab rolls
directions: Mix together.
Form into a roll and roll in chopped pecans or use as a dip.

title: fruit filled bread rolls
directions: Soak fruit overnight; boil until tender.
Chop and sweeten with honey.

title: fourteen day pickles
directions: Make brine of barrel salt and 1/2 gallon water. Place cucumbers in brine for 8 days. Pour off brine. Cover cucumbers in water mixed with alum and let stand for 24 hours. Pour off and cover cucumbers with clear water and let stand for 24 hours.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare cake mix using Egg Beaters and amount of water indicated on package.
While cake is baking, cook pineapple in saucepan 5 minutes (do not drain pineapple).

title: sausage loaf
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Divide bread in half.
Roll both halves like pie crust, in oblong shape.
Place all other ingredients in bowl and mix together.
Place half of mixture on each piece of dough and spread.
Roll each jellyroll fashion; tuck ends.
Brush with melted butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Brush again with melted butter when they come out of oven.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine next 5 ingredients in large bowl; stir well.
Add flour mixture and all other ingredients to egg/oil mixture and stir well.
Prepare 3 (8-inch) cake pans by greasing pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing.
Peel wax paper and cool.
Frost, cover and refrigerate.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute celery and onion in potatoes.
Add potatoes, 2 cups water and bouillon cube.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Add fish and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except pepper and parsley.
Simmer 10 minutes; do not boil.
Garnish with pepper and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: merk's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together.
Add creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream and blending after each addition.
Spread half of mixture in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Add nuts; mix well.
Dot batter in pan evenly with half the nut mixture.
Cover with remaining butter; dot with remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: cherry cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar into a mixing bowl. Blend in the butter or shortening until it resembles a coarse corn meal, using a pastry blender or two knives.
Add the egg and vanilla.
Mix until the dough sticks together in a ball.
Line bottom of pan.
Prick pastry with a fork to prevent puffing while baking.
Bake oven temperature at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with 1/2 pound Velveeta, sliced cheese spread.
Heat until melted.

title: surprise orange jello
directions: Mix all together well and pour in mold or chill in bowl.

title: superb steak rolls
directions: Pound steak to 1/2-inch thickness.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic.
Layer spinach, ham, cheese and egg in that order. Roll tightly and tie with a string.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour; cut into slices.

title: pastel cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, Jell-O, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in 400° oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: swiss beans
directions: Heat green beans and drain.
Pour beans in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion.
Gradually add sour cream.
Stir until thickened. Pour over beans.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: open faced raisin pie
directions: Mix together and last mix in the 4 beaten egg whites.
Pour in uncooked pie crust.
Bake slow at 325° for 1 hour; watch closely. Makes 2 small pies or 1 very large one.

title: skillet corn
directions: Cut corn off the cob.
Place in a 10-inch skillet.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, water and margarine.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine milk and flour and add to first mixture.
Cook 5 minutes longer. Add crumbled crisp bacon.

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook chopped onion, celery and carrots in olive oil until tender.

Add oregano, pepper and garlic (crushed) and cook for 1 minute more. Add Grape-Nuts, tomatoes and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: greek marinade(for pork, chicken or beef; excellent for pork chops)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Marinate meat in mixture for at least one hour before broiling.

title: peanut butter-chocolate bonbons
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Oil a baking dish.
Wash peppers, remove seeds, dry and lay peppers in pan.
Cover with cheese and eggs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 36.

title: vivian's blueberry muffins
directions: Measure first 5 ingredients into bowl and mix.	Gently fold in blueberries.
Pour into muffin cups, and bake at 375° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all and chill.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Blend in rest of the ingredients.
Turn into ungreased casserole (2 quart) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven while hot; beat well with a wooden spoon.
Cool and form into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Yields about 36 cookies.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Combine curry powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; sprinkle over chicken, each side of chicken surface.
Set aside.
In large skillet, combine orange juice, rice, water, brown sugar, mustard and remaining salt; mix well.
Place chicken breasts over rice. Bring to a boil.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand, covered, until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and rub skin with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool to touch.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully hull out pulp into a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese and paprika.
Beat until fluffy.
Stuff back into shells.
Garnish with cheese and paprika. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Bring water and oleo to boil.
Take off heat; add flour.
Add eggs one at a time.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
In a bowl mix cream cheese and pudding.
Spread onto crust.
Top with Cool Whip and decorate with chocolate sauce.

title: tango lemon pie
directions: Combine crumbs, nuts and butter.
Press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool thoroughly. Beat cottage cheese on highest speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Prepare pudding mix as directed, except use the 1 3/4 cups milk.
Stir in cottage cheese and lemon peel.
Pour into cooled crust.
Top with sour cream.
Chill several hours.

title: basic biscuit mix
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder well. Cut in shortening to size of small peas.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, pineapple juice and ginger ale in a punch bowl. Then drop sherbet in by spoonfuls.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage casserole #1
directions: Brown meat, celery,
onion and salt.
In a kettle, cook cabbage for 5 minutes.
After it starts boiling, drain and add meat mixture.
Add rice.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and potato skillet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown ham in butter and brown sugar. Remove ham and pour off drippings.

title: bacon cornbread muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir together eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and margarine, then combine with dry ingredients. Divide in two greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
(Beat after each one.)
Blend in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Butter and flour a 1 pound empty coffee can and pour in batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Remove cake when cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use large plastic bag.
Add cinnamon and sugar.
Place biscuit pieces into bag and shake until each piece is well coated.
Place biscuits into butter greased tube pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in 375° oven until brown.
Best to eat warm.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small mixing bowl combine apples and lemon juice, tossing to coat; add water, honey and cinnamon, mixing well.
Transfer to 2 cup casserole; dot with margarine and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake until apples are soft, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: ham-chicken bake with yam biscuits
directions: Place diced ham and chicken in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Stir in broth and cream.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add seasonings, onion and mushrooms.
Pour over ham and chicken.
Top hot mixture with Yam Biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix grated cheese, flour and sausage together well.
Make into small balls and cook 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: green chile enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add chopped chilies, milk and soup.
Bring to a slow boil.
Fry tortillas about a minute or less.
Layer in casserole tortillas, sauce, onions and cheese.
Repeat until tortillas and sauce are used.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: sour tart lemon bars
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, confectioners sugar and oleo together.
Beat eggs, sugar, lemon juice, 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Keep separate.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan the first mixture; bake this crust at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour lemon mixture over this crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle additional confectioners sugar on tops.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble. Brown beef in drippings; pour off fat.
Add soup, wine, parsley and pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Add onions and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 1 hour more, or until beef is tender.
Serve over wide noodles.
Garnish with bacon and parsley.

title: tom hutchins' texas millionaires
directions: Mix all ingredients except one cup of milk.
Stir well.
Let come to a good boil, stirring constantly.
Add the other cup of milk slowly; do not stop boil.
Cook until it forms a soft ball (this takes a long time).
Add pecan halves and beat until thick. Drop by teaspoon on greased pan.
Let stand until firm.
Stick toothpick in fondant and dip in chocolate mix.
Set on wax paper to cool.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies with wood mallet.
Add margarine and mix. Press into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or pan, or individual plastic cups to serve at a party.
Reserve some of this mixture for topping.
Using an electric mixer, beat pudding and milk in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix all the other ingredients and blend with pudding mixture.
Pour over crushed cookie crust and sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
(Can also make in individual pie pans.)

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together, flour, sugar and soda. Combine eggs & buttermilk. Stir into flour mixture. Beat until smooth, bake on hot griddle. Serve with butter & syrup. Makes 18

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Mix well.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Grease foil generously. Pour pumpkin batter into pan and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, no longer.

title: pig-out cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges, oil and eggs together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix Cool Whip, pineapple and vanilla pudding together and spread on cooled cake.
Keep cool.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar and water; bring to boil and boil until soft ball stage.
Take off stove and add cinnamon; stir.
Add nuts and stir until nuts are coated with sugar.
Spread on wax paper.
Spread nuts out.
Add salt to taste.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until completely tender. Add milk and 1/2 cheese. Heat slowly, stirring often, until sauce is thickened.
Do not overcook.
Put macaroni, cheese and sauce into baking dish in alternate layers. Cover with cracker crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake at 400° until bubbly and lightly browned.
Makes 2 medium size dishes.
If prepared for freezer, do not add cracker crumbs nor bake.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
For best results, put in crock-pot and allow to cook 2 hours.

title: macaroni and shrimp dinner
directions: Bring macaroni to boil; drain.
Add and mix cheese, cooked shrimp, green onions, bell pepper and white onion, chopped.
Put together in casserole bowl.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper. Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In large covered pan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling salted water 5 to 8 minutes or desired tenderness.
Drain. Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrot. Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and butter. Spread half of stuffing mix in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon squash on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Boil until salt is dissolved.
Take off heat and add the other ingredients.
Knead well for 5 minutes.
Keeps in an airtight container.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread and roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Saute onion and pepper in butter. Spread over bread.
Layer beef, ham and turkey. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over meat and then Swiss cheese. Roll like jelly roll and pinch each end together.
Lay on greased cookie sheet and bake until golden brown at 375°.
Slice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift the flour and mace together and add to butter mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken perfection
directions: First, make Curry Glaze.
Double the recipe if you like lots of sauce.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan and melt in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Mix together and press into pan. Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool good before cutting.

title: date cocoa cake
directions: Mix dates, soda and water and let stand.
(I usually use Date Crystals which are dried,
chopped dates, not so difficult to handle.) Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Cream remaining ingredients.
Add	dry
ingredients
to
creamed
mixture alternately with liquid.
Mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup chopped
nuts
and
1/2 cup chocolate chips (1/2 of 6 ounce package).
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or longer until tester comes out clean.

title: cold rice salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and add a small amount of mayonnaise to which a dash of curry powder has been added.
Mix well and add some of the artichoke juice, if needed for consistency.
Let stand overnight.
Chicken or shrimp can be added for a
variation of the recipe.

title: lemon-soy sauce chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, lemon juice, brown sugar and ginger.
Pour over wings in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Marinate overnight, mixing occasionally.
Next day, place wings in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle a little of the sauce over the wings, discarding the rest.
Arrange all wings with the tips up.
Bake for 1 hour or until wing tips are brown and crisp at 350°.

title: cooked play dough
directions: This has a wonderfully smooth texture.
Your children love it. Can add color and flavorings for smell.

title: cherry blinks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto cereal.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased sheet.
Top with cherry.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: canned spareribs
directions: Cut pork spare ribs in lengths that will pack into jars. Add 1 teaspoon salt to 1-quart. Place a small piece of fat meat on top.
Seal and process for 75 minutes at 10 pounds pressure (pressure canner).

title: spicy guacamole
directions: Using fork, mash avocado with lime juice in small bowl.
Add cilantro, chopped onion, chopped garlic, serrano chilies, chopped tomatoes and salt to combine.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: homemade tomato bisque soup
directions: Use any meat, boiled in water in a medium saucepan.
Open refrigerator, find leftovers.
Add any of your leftovers to the soup.
Add some fresh vegetables too.
Dice potatoes.
Add soup seasoning, oregano, basil, beef or chicken cubes, salt and pepper.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted boiling water until tender.
Arrange broccoli in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Trim with pimiento strips.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle lightly with Mrs. Dash seasoning.
Top with cheese slices. Combine soup and wine.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted margarine over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients well; shape into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika, or roll in chopped pecans.
Spread on crackers.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Roast the peppers in a moderate oven to loosen skin and cook peppers.
Don't blacken the skin.
Clean the peppers and cut into strips.
Place a layer of peppers in the bottom of a dish. Place the anchovies over the peppers and season lightly with salt and generously with pepper.
Add a pinch of oregano, a few capers and some of the garlic.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients and cover with olive oil.
Allow to marinate in the refrigerator. Remove garlic after 24 hours.
Serve at room temperature.
Enjoy with thinly-sliced baguettes or crackers.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti. Dice all the vegetables small. Mix.
Let set overnight.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and store. Use 3 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup water.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Grease
casserole
dish.
Mix corn and beans well.
Put in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix
next
four
ingredients and put over beans and corn mixture.
Melt
butter
(a
stick) and crush 1 roll of Ritz crackers
and
cup slivered almonds. Mix and put on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil 2 cups water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon together for 10 minutes.
Make strong tea separately.
Then mix all ingredients and mixtures together.
Serve hot or cold.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time and cream again.
Add vanilla, then fold in flour.
Place on greased cookie sheet in small pats the size of marbles.
You can decorate with chocolate bits, pecans or coconut.
Bake in 350° oven from 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cabbage soup(very different. very italian.)
directions: In a deep pan, such as a Dutch oven or deep casserole, place a layer of bread.
Top with half the cabbage.
Top that with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with parmesan and some bacon.
Repeat bread, cabbage, cheeses, and bacon.
Press down with the heel of your hand.
Boil enough chicken broth to fill just below top layer of cabbage (about 1 inch below top of cabbage).
Top with last layer of bread.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
If bread gets too brown lower temperature a bit.
This will bake up like a souffle, so don't cover.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Scald milk (uncovered).
Do not boil.
Melt butter in another pan over low heat.
Add flour gradually, stirring.
Add hot milk gradually and shredded cheese.
Stir over low heat until it thickens.
Season and serve hot.
Scalding the milk makes mixing easier and helps avoid lumps.

title: shrimp elegant
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy sauce pan and cook on low until it thickens.
Add seasonings and continue to thicken. It won't be very thick.
Add parmesan cheese.
Meanwhile, sautee shrimp in olive oil until just pink. After removing shrimp, place mushrooms and onions in same pan. Sautee until done.
Serve shrimp, mushrooms and sauce over pasta. Salad and garlic bread make this an elegant meal!!

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in the red wine vinegar, chicken broth, green pepper, pimiento, soy sauce, garlic powder and ground ginger.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 1/4 cups sauce.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beef and cabbage quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix hash, flour and 2 eggs.
Press mixture against bottom and sides to within 1-inch of top of ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9-inch. Bake meat crust 25 minutes.
Remove meat crust from oven and drain.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: low-fat banana blueberry pie
directions: Cream together sour cream, cream cheese and Equal.
Layer sliced bananas in pie shell.
Add creamed mixture.
Top with blueberries.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put in a 6 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add enough water too cook the macaroni. Add onion flakes and salt.
When macaroni is done, add the other ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes. Pour in casserole dish and add cheese.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add eggs, one at a time. Then add milk and vanilla.
Start in cold oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red beet jelly
directions: Boil the beets with water for 20 minutes.
Drain the juice off and use in the making of the jelly.

title: whipped carnation instant candy(also known as marshmallow candy)
directions: To make
instant
milk:
Mix
1/2 cup dry milk with 1/2 cup ice water.
Whip until soft peaks form.
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Whip
until
stiff
peaks form.
Combine 1/2 cup water and gelatin in large mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, syrup and 3/4 water
in saucepan.
Cook
over
medium heat, until syrup reaches
rolling boil,
stirring
constantly.
Cook 5 minutes without stirring. Pour
hot syrup over gelatin and stir until gelatin dissolves. Add vanilla.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Slice green onions.
Discard green part and use white sliced part only.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Firmly press slightly softened ice cream into graham cracker crust.
Top ice cream with fudge topping and pecans or almonds. Freeze pies for 3 hours or until firm.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave on Defrost or Low, stirring every 30 seconds.
Remove.
Add nuts and pretzels.
Spread on wax paper in thin layer. Cool on counter and break when hardened. Store in covered tin.

title: joe bailey cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar; add egg yolks to creamed butter and sugar, then add dry ingredients (sifted together) with buttermilk and coffee.
Add vanilla and nuts; fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in 2 greased cake pans at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Chocolate icing or any kind you prefer.

title: cornbread dressing(small version)
directions: *Our family loves turkey, so we bake several of them each year.
Save the excess liquid from the baked turkey and store it in the freezer.
After chilled, remove the excess fat that has formed on top and discard.
Use the remaining portion of this liquid to add a delicious flavor to the dressing.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Coat bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with butter.
Press small portion of mixed cheeses to bottom of the pan until entire bottom is coated with cheese.
To remaining cheese, add the eggs, evaporated milk and asparagus (can substitute 1 can with a can of mushrooms).
Mix together.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue swedish meatballs
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well.
Form all ingredients into balls and place in rows in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add to the butter and egg mixture. Mix well and add rest of ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower; drain and set aside in baking dish.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch glass dish with Pam.
Pour 1 box of Cheddar croutons in the glass dish.
Cover with 1 pound of ham or sausage (diced).
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups of shredded yellow cheese.
Beat 6 eggs with 2 cups of milk, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 squirt of mustard. Pour mixture over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until brown (about an hour).

title: yankee crab salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
In small bowl, stir together all dressing ingredients.
In large bowl, place pasta and all salad ingredients.
Add dressing; toss to coat well.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; remove skins and cream while hot. Add butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ambrosia balls
directions: Grind wafers until crumb consistency. Combine remaining ingredients (except coconut) and mix thoroughly. Form into small balls about the size of a marble.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar. These can be refrigerated until needed.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare in 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans into pan. Mix 1 box German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar until well blended.
Drop by spoon over cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: saag paneer(indian recipe)
directions: Warm about 4 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Add cumin seed, bay leaf, cinnamon stick and cloves.
When spices darken (2 to 4 seconds), add chopped onions, garlic and ginger.
Saute until onions are transparent.

title: toffee apple salad
directions: Wash and chop apples.
Crush Heath bars into bite size pieces. Mix with Cool Whip and chill.

title: birthday party mix
directions: Open and mix all ingredients, then divide equal amounts into Ziploc bags.

title: steak & pepper pita's
directions: 1. In medium bowl mix London Boil, Soy Sauce, Sherry, Cornstarch, Garlic Powder, and Sugar.
Set aside. 2. Cut onion and peppers in thin slices.
Cook in a skillet over medium heat until vegetables are tender crisp.
About 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside vegtables. 3. In same skillet over high heat add 3-4 tablespoons salad oil.
Cook mixture stirring quickly.
When it starts to thicken add water.
When it is almost done add vegetables.
Serve in Pita bread.

title: chicken excelsior house
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder.
Melt butter and add paprika and lemon juice.
Roll chicken in butter mixture and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender. Make sauce of sour cream, wine, mushrooms and pepper.
Pour over chicken and bake 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in mixing bowl; add oil, eggs and vanilla and beat.
Then stir in apples and nuts.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and peaches evenly in pan.
Arrange cherries in sugar mixture.
Add enough water to peach syrup to make 1 1/3 cups liquid.
Add this liquid and 2 eggs to the cake mix.
Pour over fruit; bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then turn upside down.

title: corny cheese chowder
directions: In covered saucepan, simmer vegetables (except corn) in water with bouillon, salt and pepper 10 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour; cook about 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Then add milk and heat to boiling, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce heat and add cheese; stir until melted.
Add undrained vegetables and corn with liquid.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: swiss venison
directions: Coat
venison with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown sides in cooking oil.
Add onion slices, tomatoes and water.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: best ever rum cake
directions: Too many husbands are spoiled by improper cooking.
Some are kept in hot water too long.
Others are frozen, some are always in a stew and some constantly in a pickle.
Naturally, they'll never be good and tender managed this way.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and celery together 5 minutes.
Blend soup, Cheez Whiz and hot water.
Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Separate each chicken wing into 3 sections, discarding the tip section.
Rinse, then pat with paper towels.
In an electric skillet, combine soy sauce, water, sugar and ginger; bring to a boil.
Add chicken wing pieces.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Remove cover; simmer 15 to 30 minutes or until chicken separates from bone.
Makes 20 pieces.

title: old fashion macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain off water.
Pour milk in pan. Add cheese and butter.
Cook until cheese is melted on low heat. Stir all ingredients together and place in Pyrex dish.
Top with shredded cheese and place in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: lime jello delight
directions: Make jello and let cool, then add all other ingredients. Stir well. Place in refrigerator until jelled.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out on floured board.

title: spanish rice
directions: In oil on heavy skillet over medium heat, saute rice until lightly brown; stir often.
Add onion, celery and pepper and saute 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer (over low heat), covered, 15 minutes.
If it appears a little dry, add 1/4 cup water and simmer 3 minutes longer.
Turn off fire and let stand, covered, 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate 4 hours before serving with your favorite veggies.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Top may be a little shaky when it's finished, but it will set.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain vegetables and mix with other ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: 7-up baked sweet potatoes
directions: Slice sweet potatoes into baking dish.
In skillet, combine brown sugar, salt, butter, 7-Up and spices; bring to a boil for 6 minutes.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake until done.

title: witch's brew
directions: In 30-cup coffeepot, mix cranberry juice and apple juice.
In basket of coffeepot, put brown sugar, salt, cinnamon sticks and whole cloves.
Percolate until done.

title: anchovy dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with raw bell peppers, cucumbers, carrots, cauliflower, jicama and other favorite vegetables.
This dip sounds odd, but is terrific with raw vegetables.

title: swiss style venison
directions: Roll meat in seasoned flour and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until tender.
I put it in a crock-pot.

title: just a trifle
directions: Cut cake into 3 lengthwise layers.
Sprinkle each layer with about 1 1/2 tablespoons of liqueur.
Cut cake into 1-inch cubes. Layer half the cake cubes, pudding, whipped cream and strawberries in 1 1/2-quart serving bowl (glass).
Repeat layering once. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fried ice cream balls
directions: Scoop 12 (4 ounce) balls of ice cream and freeze 2 to 3 hours. Roll ice cream balls in crushed cereal.
Dip in egg, then roll again in cereal.
Refreeze for several hours.
Deep-fry ice cream balls (no more than 2 at a time) for 30 to 40 seconds.
Drain, garnish and serve immediately.
Fun for party guests to prepare together.

title: pineapple refrigerator pie
directions: Mix and pour into crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with a variety of vegetables.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach very dry.
Mix all together and let chill 5 to 8 hours. Great with fresh vegetables.

title: strawberry party cake
directions: Cut cake in 3 layers lengthwise.
Crush strawberries.
Add sugar and cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place mixture between 3 layers.
Frost entire cake.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces on top, cover pan with foil.
Cook 1 hour and 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cavitini
directions: Cook noodles as directed. Drain. Brown sausage, peppers and onions. Drain. Mix noodles and meat mixture with all other ingredients except cheese. Place in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macs shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Break bread into quarter pieces.
Break cheese into bite-size pieces.
Arrange shrimp, bread and cheese in several layers in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour margarine over mixture. Beat eggs, add mustard and salt.
Then add milk, mix and pour over casserole.
Let stand minimum of 3 hours, preferably overnight in refrigerator, covered.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for 1 hour. When doubling recipe, use 3 pounds shrimp.

title: mary's irish stew
directions: In a 10-quart Dutch oven, add 8 quarts water.
Heat to boil. Add stew meat, carrots, celery, potatoes, bouillon cubes and onion soup mix.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Mix a double batch of Bisquick dumplings, put on top of boiling stew and cook 15 minutes longer than package directions.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix all together in order.
Chill in shallow dish.
Serves 8.

title: ginger marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This is a good marinade for beef on the grill.
Also great to cook with roast in the crock-pot, then thicken juices for gravy.
Stores well for long period of time.

title: margarita pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Combine pretzel crumbs, margarine and sugar; press on bottom and up side to rim of buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: chocolate nut sundae
directions: Crumble Oreos. Lay thin layer of Oreos in bottom of container. Cover with 1/2 of chocolate syrup. Sprinkle 1/2 chopped nuts over these layers. Top with Cool Whip. Repeat all layers once more, ending with Cool Whip. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: cheese delight
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine ingredients in crock-pot. Cook on low until cheese is melted.
Quick and easy!
Serve with Tostitos or Doritos.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Make yellow cake according to directions on box in round pans. Cool.
Slice in half horizontally.
Mix together boiling water and strawberry jello; add thawed strawberries.
Refrigerate until gels. (Won't really get thick.)
Make instant vanilla pudding according to directions.
In punch bowl, pour a ladle of strawberry filling. Then put 1 layer of cake.
Top with pudding and a heaping tablespoonful of Cool Whip.
Pour a ladle of strawberry filling, then alternate cake, pudding, Cool Whip, strawberry jello, etc. Refrigerate.
Before serving, put the rest of the Cool Whip on.
A hit at parties!

title: shrimp jambalaya(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Saute onion in butter lightly. Add flour and stir until browned. Add water and stir constantly, forming a smooth paste. Add parsley, thyme, bay leaf, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic powder and rice. Add and cook over low heat until rice is tender, stirring as needed. Add shrimp and white wine and warm thoroughly.

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Shake well in a jar.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: apricot tea
directions: Bring 3 cups of water to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Place tea bags in water and cover.
Steep for about 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add remaining water, apricot nectar, and lime juice.
Serve over ice.

title: quick cheese dip
directions: In a serving dish, layer the following ingredients in order: bean dip, mashed avocado, sour cream, chopped tomatoes, chopped black olives, shredded Cheddar cheese and chopped green onions. Chill and serve with corn chips.

title: tommy's delight
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour milk over crumbs.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips, then coconut and nuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into small squares.
Remove from pan.

title: diane's chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, drain off any grease.
Put the ground beef in crock-pot.
Pour in the catsup.
Rinse bottles out with a little water, pour water out of bottles in crock-pot, about a cup or so of water should be enough.
Add chopped pepper and onion.
Stir in the mustard, sugar, black pepper and chili powder, stir up. Simmer in crock-pot for about 5 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add a little water during cooking if you need to.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Mix ingredients in pressure cooker and cook for 15 minutes when knob is rocking.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, vinegar, and water.
Add granulated alum. Pour over pickles with celery seed added to the jar.
We keep a jar of these pickles in the refrigerator at all times.

title: marinated tri-tips
directions: Place tri-tips in Ziploc bag. Add marinade and refrigerate 2 to 3 days. When barbecuing, use marinade for basting. Test meat with thermometer; 140° rare, 145 to 150° medium to medium-rare. Serve with fresh salsa. Recipe can be reduced in half.

title: tabouleh
directions: Soak 1 cup fine cracked wheat for 15 minutes.
Rinse in cold water.
Squeeze excess water.
Put in bowl.
Add chopped tomatoes, parsley and onion.
Toss with olive oil, lemon and salt.

title: super easy salmon cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix salmon, egg, olive oil, green onions and 2/3 cup cracker crumbs. Form mixture into 8 equally sized patties. Coat patties with remaining cracker crumbs and arrange in a single layer on a medium baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes in preheated oven, turning once, until golden brown.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: In a bowl, mix the oil, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in the oatmeal, baking soda and salt.
Add the milk and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: low-fat "apple brown" betty(135 calories and 3 grams fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking dish with nonstick spray.
Coat surface of pan lightly with bread crumbs. (Reserve leftover bread crumbs.) Grate 1 teaspoon of lemon peel and squeeze 1 tablespoon from lemon (set juice aside).
In small dish, combine lemon peel, sugar and cinnamon.
Peel and core apples; cut into thin slices.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook chicken in water; save broth. Debone chicken and pull into pieces.
Mix soups, tomatoes and 1 cup broth from chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Crush chips in bag.
Spray large casserole with vegetable spray.
Place crushed chips in bottom.
Add chicken, then pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil and pour over jello.
Let cool.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: five bean salad
directions: Rinse red kidney beans.
Drain all beans.
In a separate bowl, combine oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Mix well.
Add to beans. Refrigerate.
Marinate for at least 6 hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add onion, grated carrot, sour cream and soup.
Melt margarine and mix with bread crumbs.
Place 1/2 of bread crumbs in bottom of dish and pour squash mixture over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on top and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour	into 9-inch pan well-greased
with margarine.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Good served with scoop of ice cream.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll 1/4 of the dough at a time into a circle and spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Place a peeled, cored apple in the center of the pastry and fill up hole with sugar, cinnamon and a dab of butter.
Fold up pastry around apple and prick with a fork.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat with mixer for 5 minutes.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except whipped cream; mix until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream, if desired.
Yields 2 servings.

title: bing cherry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
After draining juice from Bing cherries, add water to equal 2 cups, then mix with dissolved jello.
Fold in Bing cherries.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate overnight to congeal.
Serves 24.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix pepper, garlic and sugar together.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand until dissolved.

title: veggie bites
directions: Unfold crescent rolls and place in bottom of an ungreased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Pinch the edges to seal.
Brush dough with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing; beat.
Spread mixture on crust.
Sprinkle with cheese and vegetables.
Chill 2 hours.

title: trio beans
directions: Combine the onions, hot dogs, lima beans, kidney beans and baked beans.
Mix together the brown sugar, catsup, vinegar and mustard and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: super sloppy joe
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except bread and cheese.
Cover and cook on medium for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut top off bread.
Scoop out center to fill with lettuce and meat.
Top with tomato and cheese.

title: quick and easy alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter in a medium, non-stick saucepan over medium heat. Add cream cheese and garlic powder, stirring with wire whisk until smooth. Add milk, a little at a time, whisking to smooth out lumps. Stir in Parmesan, pepper, lemon-pepper and parsley. Remove from heat when sauce reaches desired consistency. Sauce will thicken rapidly upon cooling; thin with milk if cooked too long. Toss with hot pasta to serve.

title: 24 hour lemon pudding salad
directions: Drain fruit; set aside.
Mix egg yolks, 1/4 cup cream, lemon juice and sugar.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool. Add whipped cream.
Add fruit and marshmallows.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Makes 8 servings.
(You can use whipping cream for both and also bottled lemon juice.)

title: date logs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large saucepan; cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add rice cereal and nuts alternately, mixing well after each addition. Shape into logs and roll in coconut.
Cool and slice.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, celery and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle on still frozen peas, then a light sprinkling of sugar and salt. Spread mayonnaise like frosting over peas.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with bacon and decorate with the tomatoes and egg slices.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat butter and soup in a large saucepan.
Add potatoes, cheese and sour cream.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir gently.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
(May be frozen at this point.)
Top with green onions.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cucumber and onions
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, Miracle Whip and cream (milk).
Slice cucumbers and onion, then add to sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Let stand in refrigerator.
Keep dressing; add more cucumbers and onion.

title: molasses cookies(makes 24 large, flat cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; add sugar and molasses and mix well.
Add lightly beaten egg and blend well.
Sift flour with spices, salt and soda.
Add to first mixture; mix.
(Batter will be wet.)
Drop tablespoon of batter onto foil covered cookie sheet.
Leave 3 inches between cookies as they will spread.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until cookies start to darken.
Remove from oven while soft; let cool on foil.

title: stromboli
directions: Allow dough to rise for about 2 hours in a warm area.
While dough is rising, cook sausage and allow to drain extremely well.
This is very important.
Save a little of the sausage grease and saute the mushrooms and onions it.
When dough is ready, roll it out in a rectangular fashion. Spread mustard over the entire surface of the dough.
Layer it with sausage, mushrooms, onions, cheese, salami and ham.
When layering is complete, fold the edges of the dough together and pinch together real well. Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
About 10 minutes before it is done, spread butter on the top and allow it to brown.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 4 minutes on High and stir well.
Add peanuts, stir and cook 3 1/2 minutes on High.
Stir butter and vanilla and cook 2 more minutes on High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until foamy.
Quickly spread onto lightly greased baking sheet, spreading thin.
Makes 1 pound.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix first the dry ingredients well.
Add papple (undrained), bananas, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Blend well; do not beat.
Grease tins or use paper baking cups.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° for medium size muffins.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: mother's grape and apple jelly
directions: Prepare as grape jelly on Sure-Jell box.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In small bowl, mix soup and sour cream.
In saucepan, melt butter and cook onion and chili powder until tender.
Stir in chicken, chilies and 2 tablespoons of soup mixture; remove from heat.
Spread 1/2 cup of soup mixture in baking dish.
Spread chicken filling (about 1/4 cup) on tortilla and roll up.
Place in baking dish.
Spread remaining soup mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Place half of cornbread chunks in bottom of a large serving bowl.
Top with half of drained beans.
Combine tomatoes, pepper and onions; layer half of this mixture over beans.
Layer half of cheese, bacon, corn and reserved salad dressing.
Repeat layers, using remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook jello, sugar, water and cornstarch together until it turns clear and a little thick, about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Add fresh strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until firm and serve with whipped cream.

title: daddy's muscadine wine
directions: Mash grapes.
Put in churn with 2 1/2 pounds sugar.
Let ferment for at least a week.
When through fermenting, strain to remove skins.
Return to churn with 10 pounds sugar.
Let ferment another week or two.
Pour into bottles or jugs.

title: macaroni cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; wash.
Beat eggs and add milk and salt.
Layer macaroni and grated cheese.
Add a pat of butter to cheese.
Pour milk mixture and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Mix it all together and put on a cookie pan with a spoon. Bake in the oven for 15 or 20 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix all together and put in 2 pie shells.
