title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat egg whites until soft.
Beat yolks with milk and salt. Layer ingredients beginning with bread after removing crust and cubing bread.
Repeat layers.
Fold egg whites into milk mixture. Pour over top, cover with Sarah Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Bake the next morning at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat. Mix raisins, marshmallows and cereal into large bowl. Pour melted chocolate over ingredients in bowl and mix until well coated. Spread mixture in a buttered 8 x 8 pan. Press firmly. Chill slightly. Cut into bars, then chill until firm. Makes 16 to 18 bars.

title: apple cobbler cake
directions: Mix in a mixing bowl the sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over butter.
Add apples.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana orange bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Set aside. Blend bananas, frozen orange juice and eggs.
Stir in flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Mix until blended. Bake in a 9 x 4-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine flour, monosodium glutamate and salt.
Dip pork cubes in beaten egg and then in flour mixture; coat well.
Fry pork in deep, hot fat (360°) for 6 to 8 minutes or until browned and done. Remove and drain pork on paper towels and keep warm.
In a wok or deep skillet, combine sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice, ketchup and soy sauce; bring to boiling.
Blend cornstarch in, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Stir the warm deep fat fried pork cubes, drained pineapple chunks and green pepper pieces into the thickened sauce.
Serve while hot with steamed rice.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix everything together; add nuts.
When Jell-O is starting to set, pour into mold.
Chill for a few hours before serving.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion in the butter.
Make a white sauce with flour and milk in the butter and onion.
Add the other seasonings.
Layer this in a dish:
carrots, cheese and white sauce.
Put a topping of bits of butter and bread crumbs on and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: connecticut supper
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add water and cook slowly for 1 hour. Pour into casserole dish.
Peel and slice potatoes, thin.
Layer over meat.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over meat and potatoes. Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together and serve with chips.

title: david's rum batter
directions: Cream all of the ingredients except rum and water; freeze.
To serve, put 1 ounce of rum and 3 Tbsp. of the frozen mixture in a mug and fill with boiling water.

title: chilled vegetable salad
directions: Toss together in medium bowl.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Place cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each cupcake liner.
Mix remaining ingredients except pie filling until smooth.
Fill cupcake liners 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Place spoonful of pie filling on each.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with soda and add alternately with sour cream. Add vanilla and pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holiday fruit drops
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder and soda and stir in.
Add nuts and fruit.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry chocolate cake
directions: Drain blueberries and add enough water to bring to one cup. Set blueberries aside.
Put all ingredients except blueberries in large bowl.
Beat on low for 30 seconds, beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Fold in blueberries.
Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. After cake has cooled, prepare package of instant chocolate pudding according to instructions on package.
Pour over cake and refrigerate until pudding has set.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze and drain water from spinach. Combine all ingredients. Mix well with spinach and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: rice pudding
directions: When rice is done stir in the rest of the ingredients except cinnamon. Pour in covered dish and bake 40 minutes. Sprinkle top with butter and cinnamon. Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate eclair cake and icing
directions: Mix pudding and milk in bowl.
Beat on low speed until thick (approximately 2 minutes).
Fold in La Creme topping.
Put layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and then spread the rest of the pudding over them.
Top with final layer of crackers.
Spread icing over the top layer of crackers and chill for at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together in large bowl with electric mixer.
Mix 8 cups of bread flour with 4 tablespoons yeast.
Add this to the liquid ingredients and beat with mixer until smooth. Transfer mixture to a very large bowl or dishpan.
With a wooden spoon, stir in about 2 1/2 more cups of flour.
Let dough rise until double, usually about 45 minutes.
Now melt 2 more sticks of butter in a skillet.
Spread part of dough out on the counter and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in rounds with small biscuit cutter. Dip each round in melted oleo and place in pan to rise again. When rolls in pans have risen, bake in 375° oven about 18 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and cut up apples.
Put in bowl with cut up banana.
Add nuts, Miracle Whip and sugar.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serves about four.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Use for layer 3.

title: chicken with 7-up
directions: Marinate chicken in garlic, soy sauce, sugar, salt and pepper for 15 minutes.
Add 7-Up and lemon and let stand (covered) for 30 minutes.
Place in a covered pan, add bay leaf and cook over medium to high heat.
Let boil, then simmer for 20 minutes or until done. Garnish with spring onion.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken, in a bowl with rice.
Stir well.
Grease an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Pour ingredients into pan. Place pieces of seasoned chicken on rice and cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 400°.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and season with garlic salt and pepper. Spoon into flour tortillas, roll and place into large baking dish.

Spoon half of sauce over top. Sprinkle generously with cheese and bake at 375° until bubbly (about 20 minutes). If you do not like the cheese browned, add cheese last 5 minutes of baking. Heat remaining sauce in microwave to spoon over enchiladas at serving time.

title: breakfast before
directions: Saute sausages and drain.
Beat eggs with milk and mustard. Layer the bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread and butter  pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions, and pepper. Cover with salt, let stand 3 hours. Drain off liquid and rinse. Mix vinegar, sugar, turmeric, and spices. Bring to a boil, add cucumber, onion, and pepper. Heat thoroughly, but don't boil. Pack in hot jars, seal lid tightly.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs and add sour cream.
Add egg and cream mixture to dry ingredients.
Add boiling water and stir until just moistened.
Pour batter into 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until bread top is golden brown and springs back to the touch.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Bone and skin and chop to bite-size.
Place in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add onion, sage, 1 stick oleo, salt and pepper.
Let boil 5 to 8 minutes.
Add enough water to make 2 quarts.
In a large container, crumble corn bread and eggs.
Mix well and pour in a large roast pan.
Cut 1 stick oleo in slices over top.
Have your dressing pretty juicy or will be too dry when baked.
I taste mine to see if it needs more sage. You may want to add more seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (when it gets golden brown on top).

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, flour, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut & oleo. Pour in unbake pie crust.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: special k loaf(light)
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add pecans, chicken seasoning and George Washington seasoning.
Beat eggs and milk together; add dried soya meat.
Add all ingredients.

title: spiced russian tea mix
directions: Mix and store in closed jar.
Use teaspoon in 1 cup of water, hot or cold.

title: grama's pie crust
directions: Mix with mixer or with hand pie blender.
Then add 1 tablespoon vinegar and 1 egg (in a 1 cup measuring cup, fill with water).
Add to first mixture, stirring with fork.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: pretzel recipe
directions: Combine the 1/8 cup hot water and the yeast together in a large bowl and mix well. Add the brown sugar and warm water.
Add the flour slowly and mix together until dough does not stick to the sides of the bowl.

Remove dough from bowl and knead on a hard surface (cutting board) that is covered with the extra flour. Divide dough into golf ball size pieces and form into shape of pretzel. Once all dough has been used,
bring 5 cups of water to a boil in a large pan on stove.
Add a tablespoon of soda for every cup of water used.
Once water and soda are gently boiling, immerse pretzels into boiling water, one at a time, and count slowly to thirty.
Place pretzels on a greased cookie sheet that has kosher salt sprinkled on it.
Sprinkle kosher salt on top of pretzels and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add soda to dates and pour hot water over it; let stand until cool.
Cream sugar and butter; combine with dates, flour, eggs, cocoa and vanilla.
Add chocolate chips. Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remainder of chips and nuts.
Bake approximately 40 minutes; serve warm with whipped cream.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all above in mixing bowl and cover top with 1 1/2 cups crushed Ritz cracker crumbs in 1/2 stick melted oleo.
Bake in 350° oven until crackers are brown.
(I usually cook the onions and celery about 3 minutes in microwave oven before I put them in with the rest of it.)

title: family goulash
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
While noodles cook, cook and stir ground beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in drained noodles, celery, ketchup, mushrooms (with liquid), tomatoes and salt. Cook, simmer, 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spicy clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, including juice from 2 of the cans of clams.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours before serving with chips or vegetables.

title: pasta and walnut fruit salad
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions; drain.
Blend yogurt and orange juice concentrate in small bowl.
Add yogurt mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled thoroughly.

title: melon smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and process at high speed until smooth.
(Can substitute watermelon, honeydew or desired melon.)
Serves 4 (10 ounces each).
Counts as 1 milk and 1 1/2 fruit.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Mix sugar and salt with corn meal, blending well.
Add butter and pour in 1 1/2 cups boiling water, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool.
Beat eggs with baking powder until very light and fluffy.
Add to corn meal mixture.
Stir milk into mixture and pour into casserole dish. Place in pan of water and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heath candy bar
directions: Line mold with milk chocolate.
Sprinkle Heath brickle chips into mold and cap with chocolate.

title: cheese roll-ups(children's)
directions: Roll each biscuit into a 3 x 4-inch rectangle.
Place cheese strip in center.
Sprinkle with soup mix.
Roll up like a jelly roll from the long side.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix according to directions.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans for 30 to 33 minutes at 350°.
Cool layers completely.
Split each layer (you will have 4 layers).

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump pie filling and spread to cover bottom of pan.
Dump pineapple on top, undrained.
Sprinkle box of cake mix on top.
Slice margarine on top of cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Don't stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook hamburger (drain).
Peel potatoes and boil until done, drain, mash with buttermilk.
Use a large square cake pan.
Put a layer of hamburger in pan, then mashed potatoes.
Add a layer of cheese.
Cover with foil, place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle(candy)
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water in a large pan and bring to a boil until it strings.
Add peanuts and cook until it starts to turn light brown.
Then add soda and stir.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.
Break into pieces.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Blend oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix and add oatmeal.
Spread in a large jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Scatter chocolate chips on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: velveeta chicken
directions: Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Cut up velveeta and melt in hop spaghetti.
Stir in soups and tomatoes.
Add chicken.
Bake until bubble hot.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Mix all ingredients with the exception of crumbs.
Make alternate layers of crumbs and mixture. Bake in a hot 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° or 350° and bake about 20 minutes.

title: chicken romano(serve with rice or over spaghetti)
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture and brown
in
hot shortening.
Drain, leaving 1 tablespoon drippings.
Saute
onion until tender.
Add tomato juice, 2
tablespoons cheese, sugar, salt, garlic salt, oregano, basil leaves,
vinegar, mushrooms and parsley, stirring well. Return chicken
to skillet with sauce; cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheesy hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spray a miniature muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray. With 3-inch cookie cutter, cut the won ton skins into circles. Mold each won ton skin into one of the muffin cups, forming a little cup.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 7 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Remove from pan to a cookie sheet; continue with rest of won tons.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Put in already hot, greased pan, turning biscuits as they fry.
Dip (roll) into cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: deviled deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half. Remove yolks. Mash.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Refill whites.
Makes 12. Preparation time is 25 minutes.

title: creamed onions
directions: If raw onions are used, peel and place in saucepan.
Add half the salt and just enough water to cover, bring to boil, cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
While onions are cooking, melt butter in pan, blend in flour and rest of salt (or all the salt if using canned).
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add drained onions; heat to serving temperature, sprinkle with almonds and serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix first four ingredients in an ovenproof bowl.

title: spiced juice (hot)
directions: Combine apple cider, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil 5 minutes and add orange juice.

title: french toast
directions: Add salt, sugar and milk to beaten egg.
Dip bread into egg mixture.
Cook soaked slice of bread on buttered grill or in large skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Serve with maple syrup or jelly.

title: smoked turkey salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
In a small bowl, stir together remaining ingredients, except pepper. Pour dressing over salad and mix lightly.
Season with pepper. Refrigerate until chilled.
Great served with crackers.
Have a nice party.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until starts coming off bone. Remove bones.
Break chicken apart.
Add canned tomatoes, tomato sauce, V-8 juice, potatoes (cut into small pieces), margarine, chopped onion, carrots (sliced) and celery (chopped).
Cook until done.
Add butter beans and cook.
Add white corn.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes more; season to taste.
Makes about 13 quarts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease bottom of cake pan.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Put shortening in bowl.
Add sugar gradually and beat after each addition.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add apples and beat enough to blend dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Add the zucchini, pineapple, raisins and nuts. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: christine's taco dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with shredded lettuce, Cheddar cheese and chopped tomato.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soups and Ro-Tel together.
Add taco seasoning and red pepper.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix in soup mixture.
Add chicken, then tortillas.
Mixture should be moist, but not soupy.
Spread mixture into casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Let bake at 350° until hot through and through.
Spread grated cheese over top and continue to bake until cheese melts.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake until golden, about 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into small rectangles.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Use a 4-quart pot.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Make the coffee; let cool.
Add vodka to sugar-coffee mix. Add vanilla beans; mix well.
Turn occasionally.
Let stand 28 days.

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: Grease bundt pan.
Arrange frozen rolls in pan (use all of them).
Sprinkle with pudding.
Mix butter, sugar and cinnamon and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with nuts and raisins over this.
Cover with waxed paper and let rise overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.
Invert cake on plate.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine in order given.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Add pineapple, vanilla and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 20 minutes.

title: quick chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken breasts in salad dressing first, and then bread crumb mixture.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam, or lightly greased.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes, turning halfway through baking time. Serve with your choice of pasta, sauce and additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: cube steak and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper steak and then roll in flour until well coated. Fry until good and brown on both sides.
Put into crock-pot.
Add soup, water and milk to pan that steak was fried in.
Stir until it is hot.
Pour over cube steak in crock-pot.
Cook on low 4 to 6 hours.
Water or milk may need to be added to gravy if it is too thick.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Blend in sugar, spice, flour and salt; mix well.
Add milk and mix well. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
One pie yields 8 servings.

title: barbecue yoshidas chicken drummettes
directions: Marinate chicken drummettes overnight in a medium bowl with sauce.
Barbecue over hot grill or bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and pepper and soak in salt water for 1 hour, then drain.
Cover with ice cubes for 1/2 hour.
Mix sugar, vinegar, spices and water.
Bring to hard boil.
Put in cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Boil again for about 1 minute, hard.
Put in jars.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: In a 3 quart mixing bowl, beat eggs well.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Sift and measure flour.
Add to it the baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add this to the batter and mix until well blended.
Then stir in chopped nuts. Pour the batter into two greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.
These freeze well.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over all the other ingredients.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Top with crumbled Rice Krispies.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 5 servings.

title: date and nut rolls
directions: Cut dates up; put Rice Krispies and nuts in a bowl.
Melt butter and add sugar, dates and 1 slightly beaten egg.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Pour over rest of ingredients, except coconut. Butter hands and make small balls; roll in coconut.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Pat dough onto floured board and cut into donut shapes.
Drop in hot fat. Turn over as soon as they rise to the top, browning both sides.

title: oyster cracker appetizer
directions: Heat all ingredients except crackers.
Toss in crackers. Serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan at 350°.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Pour a box of Rice Krispies in a large flat bowl or plate. Add marshmallow cream.
Stir.
Finally, add margarine, then you'll get a luscious treat of great Rice Krispie Treats, then cool in refrigerator.

title: barbecued turkey
directions: Combine all
ingredients
except turkey and cook until well done (15 to 20 minutes).
Add
turkey
and simmer 15 minutes. Serve on buns or toast points.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed just until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: dorothy bittner's oxtails
directions: Brown oxtails in Dutch oven on top of stove.
Add vegetables to brown; sprinkle with browned flour (to brown flour, place in pan over low heat and watch carefully).
Add hot water, tomatoes and seasonings (place bay leaves and cloves in cheesecloth bag for ease of removal).
Cook, covered, in 350° oven until tender.
Serve with cooked egg noodles.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese mints(microwave)
directions: Soften cream cheese at Medium High power about 2 minutes.
Add butter and half and half.
Microwave for another 45 to 60 seconds on Medium High to High power until butter is melted.
Stir at least once.
Add frosting mix.
Micro at High power 2 minutes, stirring and whisking until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Add peppermint extract and food coloring of your choice.

title: wild chokecherry syrup
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil in a large saucepan.
Turn heat down and simmer for 15 minutes.
Skim off scum.
Pour into jars and seal.
Process in boiling hot water bath for 10 minutes. Makes 3 batches, 4 pints.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla. Beat well.
Gradually blend in flour.
Stir in oats, 1/2 cup nuts and coconut.
Spread onto lightly greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Melt over hot, not boiling, water the butterscotch morsels.
Remove from heat.
Spread evenly over cookie layer.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup nuts. Chill for 10 minutes.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 75 bars.

title: goulash
directions: Brown garlic and onion.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add tomato sauce and bring to a boil.
Add tomato juice.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with vegetable oil and pierce with fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a thin shell.
Place pulp in large bowl. Saut onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender and add to pulp along with light cream and sour cream, salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in cheese.
Stuff potato shells and place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt remaining butter and drizzle over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Potatoes can be stuffed ahead and frozen.)

title: hamburger casserole #2
directions: Pat hamburger into sides and bottom of casserole dish to form a shell.
Put a layer of potatoes, a layer of onion and another layer of potatoes.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients; set overnight.

title: chocolate fudge upside-down cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add milk.
Stir well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa.
Add to milk mixture.
Stir well. Pour into greased 9-inch round cake pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Mix together brown sugar and cocoa. Sprinkle over top of dough and nuts in pan.
Pour boiling water over all.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool in pan. Cut in wedge pieces.
Turn upside-down to serve, spoon sauce over top.
Serve with ice cream.

title: no guilt chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup. Add vegetables and chicken. Pour into casserole dish. Mix milk, egg and Bisquick into a batter and pour over chicken and vegetable mixture. Bake for 30 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.

title: overnight boston baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 200° shortly before 10 p.m.
Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven; cover.
Bake overnight; check beans at 7 a.m.
If beans seem runny, raise temperature to 350° and bake uncovered 45 to 60 minutes longer.
If baking during the day, plan on 10 hours (can use crock-pot).
Serve with Boston Brown Bread (see index).

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Punch holes in cake with fork. Pour Eagle Brand over the cake.
Then pour cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip, coconut and pineapple and spread over cake.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: In a skillet, cook the bacon until crisp.

title: cranberry pineapple relish
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
Over high heat, bring to full boil the cranberries, sugar, raisins, ginger, salt, allspice and reserved pineapple syrup; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until cranberries pop.
Add pineapple chunks and cook for 5 minutes more or until mixture thickens. Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: tofu balls
directions: Saute vegetables and basil 10 minutes in water or oil.
Add rest of ingredients; stir well.
Form into patties or balls.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown on outside, but moist inside.
Eat as is or with ketchup, tomato slices, lettuce, pickles, chips and sprouts on whole wheat, rye or pita bread.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Cut sweet potatoes in slices and put into a buttered casserole dish.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, orange rind, cinnamon and apricot juice in saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Stir in apricots, butter and pecans.
Pour over potatoes and bake in 375° oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In a large bowl, mix water with 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Peel and core apples; slice directly into lemon water. In a 6 to 8-quart, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and remaining lemon juice. Drain apples; add to sugar mixture and stir gently. Let stand 20 minutes. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring often until mixture begins to thicken, about 10 minutes. Let cool. Pack in rigid pint freezer containers or freezer jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace. Apply lids and freeze. Makes 6 pints. Stores in freezer up to 6 months.

title: liver paste
directions: Mix well together; shape into log or ball.
Chill and serve as spread on crackers.

title: red cabbage
directions: Melt the lard, or use oil, in a large pot.
Add the cabbage and the apple to the pot and stir to mix with the oil.
Cover the pot and cook over medium low heat for about 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add salt and pepper, mix.
Add the vinegar and stir well.

title: lemon walnut cake
directions: Cream together butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, sugars, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Combine beaten egg, oil and milk.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just to moisten.
Fold in pecans.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: peahi stir-fry chicken
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Slice into pieces.
Mix egg white, salt, pepper, cornstarch and sherry.
Toss with chicken.
Marinate 10 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil and salt in wok.
Saute the snow peas, mushrooms, celery and water chestnuts for 2 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in pan. Stir-fry garlic, green onions and chicken over high heat a few minutes.
Add soy and sugar.
Toss, then add cooked vegetables and stir-fry 1 minute.
Transfer to platter and serve.

title: cajun dry rub
directions: Just mix all together and put in airtight container.

title: party pistachio and sherbet cake
directions: Early in day or day ahead:
Place both containers of sherbet in refrigerator for about 20 minutes to soften slightly.
Chill 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Finely chop pistachios.
Spread half the chopped pistachios over bottom of spring-form pan.
Carefully smooth softened raspberry sherbet over pistachios, pressing with back of spoon to remove any air pockets.
With medium size ice cream scoop, scoop rainbow sherbet and place on top of raspberry layer, arranging scoops side by side in one layer.
Place in freezer while preparing pudding.

title: cheese ball no. 1
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop green onions fine, including tops. Chop
dried
beef,	mushrooms,
onions and ripe olives. Mix well. Mold
into	2 cheese balls.
Roll in chopped pecans before serving.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix milk, eggs and lemon juice well.
Add pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip, blending until smooth.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Chill several hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: springtime macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain, rinse and drain.
Cut sausages in fourths.
Combine with macaroni, pineapple, pimentos and celery. Combine mustard, sour cream, salt and paprika.
Toss with macaroni. Chill.
Fill cantaloupe halves.

title: cheese bread
directions: Blend together.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender, 15 to 20 minutes (add a little salt).
Strain.
In large baking bowl or dish, layer your macaroni, butter, Lawry's seasoned salt and garlic to taste.
Mix this, then slice your cheese on top of first layer.
Try to make 2 or 3 layers, laying cheese on top of each layer, making last layer cheese on top.
Add milk until you see it come through your macaroni.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good with baked sweet potato!

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in a large bowl until very light.
Blend in vanilla, flour and pecans.
Shape into balls about
1-inch
in	diameter.
Place
on
ungreased baking sheet. Bake
at
for 20 minutes;
cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: golden pork chops
directions: Combine golden onion soup mix with bread crumbs. Dip chops in eggs, then bread crumb mixture, coating well.
Place in lightly greased large shallow baking pan; drizzle with melted butter (optional).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, turning chops once. Makes about 8 servings.

title: baked chicken drummettes
directions: Melt butter.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Using "leg" part of wings, dip in butter, then cheese mixture.
Arrange in shallow pan or baking dish in foil.
Drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
May be prepared day before and reheated or freezes well.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: fruity cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Jell-O.
Add flour, baking powder, egg and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 14 minutes.

title: top-notch bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper cups.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined milk, molasses, oil and egg,
mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes, until golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop in hot oil by spoonful.
Fry until golden brown.

title: taco snack mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Toss well to coat. Makes about 20 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone.
Shred in pieces.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Place Doritos in casserole dish.
Spread mixture over chips.
Top with cheese, then Ro-Tel.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Spread beans in 8x8 inch pan.
Layer sour cream, gaucamole, salsa, olives and onions.
Cover with cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate a couple of hours before serving.

title: easy peach crunch
directions: Mix and sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Drop egg in dry ingredients and mix with a fork.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Melt butter and dribble over.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown and bubbling.

title: quick and easy chicken pie
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix broth and soup together and bring to a boil.
Put chicken in deep dish crust and pour liquid over top.
Make slashes in pie shell and put on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: dixie divinity
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and water over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring until forms hard ball when dropped in cold water (250°).
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Continue beating while pouring hot syrup in thin stream over egg whites.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture holds shape, then fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with margarine until smooth. Mix with other ingredients, (except rolls) until mushy.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Seal perforations.
Spoon 1/4 mixture into middle of rectangles.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center; seal.
Brush top with fresh Parmesan cheese (optional).
Bake on ungreased pan 20-25 minutes.
Use temperature on back of Crescent Roll can.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and 1 teaspoon vanilla in large mixer bowl. Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, salt, cinnamon and soda; stir into egg mixture.
Fold in carrots, walnuts and raisins. Pour into 12 x 7-inch glass baking dish, greasing bottom only. Microwave on High for 14 to 16 minutes, turning dish every 4 minutes.
Cool.

title: rice and kielbasa
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 3-quart dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°, then 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy dessert
directions: Place in 9 x 13-inch pan in the order given.
Bake at 325° in glass or 350° in metal pan for 1 hour.
Serve cold or warm with whipped cream.

title: baked stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook rice in 1 1/3 cups boiling, salted water for 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain if necessary.
Set aside.
Cut peppers in half.
Remove seeds and white membrane. Parboil peppers in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Arrange in a lightly oiled, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter in a small skillet.
Add onion, celery and sunflower seeds.
Saute until onion is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir into rice.
Add parsley, eggs, oregano, chilies, black pepper and salt to taste.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put about 1/3 cup hot water in bottom of pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes. Great served with stewed tomatoes and cornbread.
Serves 4.

title: jackie's fast ice cream dessert
directions: Divide all ingredients in half, making enough for 2 layers. Tear up cake and put 1/2 of it into a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan for the first layer.
Add 1/2 the ice cream (it will need to be softened some); this is part of the first layer also.
Top ice cream with 1/2 the fudge topping.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the crushed Heath bars (3).
Repeat for the second layer, ending with the Heath bars.
Cover with foil and re-freeze.
It will need to be softened some in order to cut for serving.

title: roll-ups
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and Ranch dip; spread on flour tortillas.
Starting at one corner, roll up and refrigerate enough to slice easy.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt butter and remove from heat.
Add milk, vanilla, salt, cocoa and sugar.
Stir well.
Put into greased 9-inch square pan. Chill for 4 to 6 hours and cut into squares.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Blend salt, lemon juice and shortening.
Add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and soda twice.
Add pineapple and flour to mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Bake for 12 minutes at 400°.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: saints delight(low sugar)
directions: Over medium heat, cook and stir gelatin, pudding mix and water until it boils, about 15 minutes.
Cook until partially set. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into 8 parfait dishes and chill.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into casserole dish.

title: maria's enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add cheese, salt and pepper. Fill tortillas with mixture and roll over and seal with toothpick. Place in oblong dish.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a salad bowl.
Combine rest of ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: biscuit spirals
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder. Cut in margarine.
Make well in center.
Add egg and milk, mixing well.
Roll out to 15 x 8-inches.
Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon on top.
Fold dough in half. Cut in 1-inch strips and twist.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald 3 1/2 cups milk over direct heat.
Mix cornmeal with remaining cup milk.
Add to scalded milk, stirring constantly. Place over boiling water (use double boiler) and cook 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add margarine, molasses, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into greased baking dish (1 1/2-quart size).
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: yeast pancakes
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together; mix well.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix buttermilk, eggs and oil;
add dry ingredients
until	well
blended.	Add yeast.
Let rise. Will keep for
or
4	days
in refrigerator.	Makes great crepes which can
be
frozen.
Make
any vegetable or meat filler for crepes.
Just use your own imagination.

title: stuffed celery
directions: In 1 cup measure, combine vegetable and onion flakes; add the water.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 20 to 45 seconds, or until flakes are soft.
Set aside.
Place cheese in small bowl.
Reduce power to (50%) Medium.
Microwave 20 to 45 seconds, or until softened.
Stir in vegetable flakes.
Stuff celery with cheese mixture.
Cut each stalk into 5 pieces. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: beef stew a la guatemala
directions: Boil 2 cups of water in a 1 quart saucepan, add rice, cook until done, about 15 minutes

title: peach crisp
directions: Put peaches in 10 x 6 1/2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix sugar and flour and spread over peaches.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Good with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: dressing for fruit salad
directions: Combine maple syrup with egg yolks, well beaten.
Cook, stirring until thick; cool.
Season with salt and fresh lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.

title: scrumptious chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
(Stir often.)
Stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon extract.
Blend well, set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients (cut butter into 1 tablespoon pieces) in food processor and pulse until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare cake.
Cool and crumble into a baking pan, using a fork.
Prepare chocolate pudding, using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Whip cream to stiff peaks.
Crush frozen Heath bars with a rolling pin. In a large glass bowl, place 1/2 of each ingredient:
cake crumbs, pudding, crushed Heath bars and whipped cream.
Repeat layers, ending with plenty of whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars or chocolate jimmies.
Incredibly delicious!!

title: steamed pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Flour each piece.
Fry in oil until done (fry in skillet).
Cover in hot water (one inch above pork chops).
Simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.
Water will turn to gravy and is great on mashed potatoes.
Can also be done with chicken.

title: mexican munch
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Melt butter over low heat.
Drizzle butter over mix, mixing well.
Bake in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Store in airtight containers.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits.
Cook (in skillet) the sausage, onion and pepper. Drain.
Layer with cheese (1 cup). Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, vanilla and jello; mix well.
Gradually add flour.
Force through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: oreo ice cream freeze
directions: Soften ice cream. Set aside. Crush cookies into fine crumbs. Mix into softened ice cream. Stir in Cool Whip and pour in 13 x 9-inch pan. Freeze until firm. Cut into squares. Enjoy!

title: pudding delight
directions: Crust:
Combine melted butter, ground pecans and flour; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: judy's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cut in cubes.
Chop eggs and add ingredients. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: lasagna soup
directions: Place meats and lasagna in large kettle.
Place all the remaining ingredients in the kettle with lasagna and meat and cook until done.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: In small bowl, mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water.
In large bowl, combine 1/4 cup soup mixture with remaining ingredients. Shape into meatballs; brown in shortening in frypan.
Or, place in glass 12 x 8-inch pan, cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes, turning dish once.
Drain fat.
Pour remaining soup mixture over and simmer 30 minutes, covered, in frypan or return to microwave for 3 more minutes.

title: easy spinach soup
directions: Heat water, bouillon granules and frozen spinach to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan; break up spinach.
Cover and cook about 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in mushrooms, pimientos, garlic salt and rosemary; heat until hot.
Garnish each serving with 1 tablespoon yogurt.

title: casa de melida supreme french dressing
directions: Combine all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Place in a large mixing bowl; set at medium speed and add vinegar.
Mix well for 1 minute.
Add salad oil slowly; blend 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice and blend 1 minute more.
Your dressing will be creamy, savory and delicious.
Yields 1 quart.

title: mennonite delight
directions: Combine butter, graham crackers and sugar in bottom of oblong baking dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes. Heat 3 tablespoons margarine in saucepan over low heat until melted. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in a large pan, greased and sprinkled with meal.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf(serves 30 to 35 people)
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in 3 or 4 large baking pans in a moderate oven 1 1/2 to 2 hours until done.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar, syrup, salt and butter for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour mixture over warmed popcorn and stir well.
Spread in pan.
Place in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl add the following: powdered sugar, 2 sticks margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 20 minutes (no less) and pour on top of crust.
Slice bananas and place on top of mixture.
Add crushed pineapple on top of bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip; add chopped pecans, if desired.
Add cherries, if wanted.
Chill at least 8 hours before serving.

title: olive craver's sugar pie
directions: Sprinkle flour over bottom of unbaked pie shell, then sprinkle with white sugar.
Next, sprinkle with brown sugar and a dash of cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Pour evaporated milk over all of it. Bake at 450° until brown.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix in plastic bag with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Pat mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Beat for 2 minutes room temperature ice cream; sprinkle instant pudding on ice cream as it is melting.
Add milk.
Pour over Ritz cracker mixture. Chill overnight.

title: chicken rice skillet
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Take out.
Pour most of oil out. Combine rest of the ingredients.
Put chicken on top.
Simmer until done.
Add water if it becomes dry.

title: candy pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff, add sugar and vanilla. Gently stir in pecans.
Coat well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave them in the oven 30 more minutes. Take out and store in an airtight container.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with Pam.
Place all cheese in pan and top with sliced jalapenos.
Mix Bisquick, 2 eggs and evaporated milk together.
Pour mix over cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese is golden brown on edges.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Beat together all ingredients until well blended.
Serve as a dip with fresh cut up fruits or pound cake cubes.
Yields approximately 3 cups.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Cut meat into large chunks; add pineapple, celery, bell pepper and onion.	Mix mayonnaise with cream, salt, pepper and vinegar. Toss well with meat mixture.
Refrigerate.	Serve on crisp greens. Serves 6-8.

title: yankee doodle dandy pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Remove from heat and beat in cream cheese and vanilla until mixture is smooth.
Pour filling into crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Arrange strawberries in circle around outer edge of pie.
Place one strawberry in center of pie.
Fill in remaining area with blueberries.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: cube steak with mushroom gravy
directions: Season cube steaks with salt and pepper. Sift flour over both sides of meat. Brown meat on both sides in hot oil in a heavy skillet. Add cream of mushroom soup that has been diluted with water. Cover pan; turn heat down to low and cook about 30 minutes until meat is fork-tender.

title: green bean casserole
directions: If using frozen green beans, precook.
Grease a casserole dish with butter.
Mix soup with milk; salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange dream dessert
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar; add boiling water and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in punch concentrate and vanilla. Combine 1/2 cup cold water with crushed ice cubes to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Stir until thickened; with whisk, blend ice cream into gelatin mixture until smooth.
Spoon into 6 dessert glasses.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Garnish with orange slices and whipped cream, if desired.

title: crock-pot wieners
directions: Cut wieners in 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Put in crock-pot.
Cover with Catalina dressing.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: quick chocolate nut fudge cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar then set aside. In sauce pan on med. heat mix: margarine, cocoa, & hot water. Beat eggs in separate cup add to sauce pan - then add buttermilk, cinnamon, soda & vanilla. Bring almost to a boil, then add to flour mixture. Grease & flour 9 x 13 pan, bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix all
ingredients and put in pie shells.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle pecans on top if desired.

title: zippy sandwich mustard
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add boiling water; stir to form paste.
Stir in vinegar and mustard.
Mix well. Store in mustard jars in refrigerator.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Spray pie pan with Canola spray.
Press graham cracker crumbs in bottom of pie pan.
Blend together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla then add egg whites.
Blend together; pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then chill.
Top with fat-free whipped topping. Add fresh fruit to garnish.

title: "riz" biscuits
directions: Mix yeast with warm buttermilk.
Add soda.
Cut the Crisco into the dry ingredients.
Slowly mix liquid mixture into the dry ingredients.
Roll out on a board and cut into biscuits. Let stand long enough to rise.
Then bake about 12 minutes in 425° oven. Makes 24.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients in order as listed except pecans and egg whites. Beat well. Add pecans. Fold in egg whites. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and add eggs, sugar, flavoring and margarine. Put in a casserole dish.
Mix last four ingredients together and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake in oven at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: tex-mex casserole dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, taco seasoning and mayo in bowl.
Use a large oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Spread bean dip on bottom; top with avocado. Layer sour cream.
Layer onions, tomatoes and olives.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve chilled.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients and freeze very well.

title: strawberry bavarian pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until thickened.

title: almond pine cones the nutsnacker
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in shallow pan. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often, until they begin to turn color. Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Add crumbled bacon, onion, dill and pepper.
Mix well. Cover and chill overnight. Form cheese mixture into pine cone shapes. Beginning at narrow end, press almond at slight angle into cheese mixture in rows.
Garnish with artificial pine sprigs.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: lemon-cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and cool; add milk and chill until partially congealed.
Stir in cottage cheese with remaining ingredients.
Serve on lettuce with cinnamon crisp or vegetable things.

title: bread 'n butter pickles
directions: Cut onions and pepper same length as cucumbers.
Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Cover with ice.
Pour 1 cup hot water on top, cover and let stand 3 hours.
Drain in colander.

title: mesir
directions: Place lentils, water, salt and garlic in a 3-quart casserole. Bring to a brisk boil; cover and lower heat.
Simmer about 1 hour. While lentils are cooking, heat oil in a frypan.
Saute onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add onion flakes, water and red pepper; simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
When lentils are done, drain and add to onion mixture.
Stir.
Cook 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: party ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain and add the cream cheese to melt.
Brown beef.
Add the other ingredients except the Cheddar cheese.
Put into a large baking or casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and sugar in crushed pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Fold into cranberry mixture along with oranges and grated rind.
Chill.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and egg whites.
Beat well. Beat egg whites separately.
Sprinkle flour on the nuts.
Fold the floured pecans and egg whites into the mixture.
Cook in a tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Dump cake onto cake plate.
Pour juice from the pineapple over the cake.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes, until top is nice and brown.

title: foil wrapped dinner
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Place frozen peas in colander or sieve.
Run water over and drain.

title: peaches n cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with a mixer for 2 minutes. Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put peaches over the batter.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth, then add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth, then fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Freeze or refrigerate until set.
Top with caramel or fudge topping.

title: broccoli and friend
directions: Plunge broccoli into boiling, salted water in vegetable steamer for 3 minutes.
Remove at once and place in colander. Repeat with cauliflower and place in colander with broccoli.
In a large skillet, melt butter until slightly brown (do not burn). Add bread crumbs and tarragon and cook 1 minute over medium heat. Toss in vegetables, seasonings and pimento.
Stir gently to coat vegetables and taste for seasoning, correcting if necessary.
Turn onto warmed platter or bowl.

title: chamberlin's cheese and broccoli soup
directions: In a stockpot or large saucepan, saute onions, garlic and celery in olive oil until tender. Turn heat to low and add all spices and herbs. Stir and let stand for 1 minute. Chop broccoli stems and leaves, reserving florets. Add chopped broccoli and diced potatoes to spice mixture. Cover with water and bring to a boil. Simmer mixture for 20 minutes. Break up and steam florets; set aside. Blend soup in the work bowl of a blender or food processor until creamy. This may need to be done in batches. Return soup to pot. Add cheese, milk and steamed florets. Heat mixture thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix and bake in a 350° oven until well done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased).

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 onion rings.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and put rest of cheese and onions on top.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Beat the eggs in mixer;
add
cups of cold water and beat. Add flour gradually.
Cook	in
inch Teflon pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Put
about
to 3 tablespoons in pan at a time.
Cook on medium
heat
on top of stove until it looks dry. Turn over for
about 30 seconds and remove.
Cool. Store in stack with flour in between.
Makes about 24.

title: 5-hour beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients gently; place in a Dutch oven pan.
Cover tightly.
Bake 5 hours at 250°.
Don't peek!

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Mix and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Drain fruit and cut up.
Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese together in a large bowl.
Stir in dry Jell-O; mix well.
Add fruit; chill until time to serve.

title: buckeyes
directions: Stir together peanut butter and margarine. Gradually add sugar, stirring to combine. Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on waxed paper. Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: layered chicken bake
directions: First, in a saucepan, mix the chicken, cream of chicken soup, evaporated milk and green chilies. Simmer for 15 minutes.

In a cake pan, first lay out 4 shells, then pour 1/2 sauce mixture, then another layer of shells, then remaining sauce. Top with cheese and 4 more shells. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: slush punch
directions: Prepare in an empty gallon milk jug.
Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and a small amount of water, then add pineapple juice.
Fill rest of jug with water and freeze.
Set out to thaw to where it is slushy, then pour cold ginger ale over it and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until blended, then add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Cook until thick enough to pour over cake.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble bread in large pan.
Melt butter or oleo and lightly saute onion and celery.
Add to crumb mixture.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
If dressing seems too dry, add more broth.
Bake in shallow pan at 400° about 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat together all but sweet potatoes.
Add sweet potatoes and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 375° until brown and done.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Blend or process first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Blend until well mixed.
Slowly add first mixture and pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill and serve with crackers.
Recipe can be made with low-fat milk, cottage cheese and mayonnaise.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mushrooms well.
Combine sugar, oil and vinegar.
Stir well.
Add green pepper and onion to oil mixture. Then add well-drained beans and mushrooms.
Keep in covered casserole in fridge.
Stir daily.
Will keep 3 to 4 weeks.

title: "dirt" pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk for 2 minutes.
Add softened smooth cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding and cookie crumbs in flower pot.
Be sure to save enough "dirt" to layer on top.
Add silk/plastic flowers on top.

title: scripture cake(from the bible)
directions: Follow Solomon's prescription for making a good boy, Proverbs 23:14, and you will have a good cake.

title: fresh cucumber pickles
directions: Slice the vegetables.
Add any other vegetables you wish. Place the vegetables in a gallon jar.
Mix the remaining ingredients together; pour over the vegetables.
Cover and keep in the refrigerator.

title: lamb's wool pie
directions: Combine milk, bananas and nuts; mix well.
Be careful not to crush bananas.
Add Cool Whip; fold well.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Chill 6 hours.

title: blueberry custard
directions: Turn unbaked pie shell into Pyrex pan from aluminum. Put on a cookie sheet. Beat together sugar, flour, oleo, eggs, vanilla and blueberries. Pour 2 cups blueberries into pie shell. Cover with custard. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw and smash Tater Tots.
Add 3/4 of the sour cream and whole can of cream of chicken soup.
Add in cheese.
Mix all together and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Pour melted butter over sugar; add egg, flavoring, flour and nuts.
Mix by hand and press in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Mix together all ingredients and place in buttered casserole.
Top with buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning per directions.
Add can of refried beans to mix.
Let simmer. Combine cornbread mixes per directions.
Add 1/2 can creamed corn and picante sauce to mixture.
Pour 1/2 cornbread into lasagna pan; top with all meat and bean mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread on top.

title: snowball dessert
directions: Beat whites to soft peaks, adding 1/2 cup sugar gradually. Continue beating until stiff.
Combine milk, water and 6 tablespoons sugar in large shallow pan.
Bring to simmer, stirring often.
With 2 spoons form snowballs of meringue.
Add to milk mixture.
Poach 2 minutes.
Turn; poach 1 more minute.
Remove with slotted spoon; drain.
Add 1/4 cup hot milk mixture to flour; blend well.
Add another 1/4 cup; stir.
Add to yolks.
Stir this into remaining milk mixture.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Let cool.
Float snowballs on top of custard. Serves 6.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Peel and slice 6 to 8 medium apples.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Make custard.
To beaten eggs, add mixture of flour, cornstarch, sugar and butter.
Then add milk and stir well.
Pour mixture over sliced apples.
Sprinkle mixture of sugar and cinnamon (to taste) over top of pie.
Place foil over pie and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and lower heat to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Make sure pie is baked until custard is completely set.
May take longer than 45 minutes.

title: johnny appleseed meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: butterhorns
directions: Allow milk to cool and add butter, sugar and salt.
Add yeast to milk mixture, then eggs and flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Set in warm place until sponge is light.
Add another 2 cups flour and knead well.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll each in circle.
Cut into small pie-shaped pieces.
Starting at wide end, roll tightly to the point.
Place on greased sheet.
Let rise.
When very light, bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Layer bread, cheese, bread and cheese.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Allow to refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, placing pan in larger pan with 1-inch of water in it.
Bake until puffed and dry on top.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into about 20 small meatballs and place into skillet.
Mix remaining soup and water.
Pour over the meatballs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Stir often (skimming off excess fat).
Good with mashed potatoes.
Can be doubled.

title: "dog food"
directions: Put all ingredients except chocolate in large container.
Melt chocolate and pour over mixture; mix well.
Turn out on waxed paper, spreading very thin.
When set, break into pieces.

title: peanut chews
directions: Combine sugar and Karo; heat to boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Stir in corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over peeled and sliced cucumbers.
Marinate at room temperature 4 hours or more.
Serve chilled, if desired.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix next 2 ingredients.
Add flour (after mixing bowls together), powder, salt and nuts to mixture.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes until toothpick tests done.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie crust in oven for 5 minutes. Dice onion and zucchini.
Place all vegetables in bottom of pie crust.
Mix eggs, milk and salsa together, then pour over vegetables.
Shred cheese and sprinkle on top of eggs and vegetables.
Bake in oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until fork stuck in center comes out clean.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Combine peas and ham in blender.
Blend well.
In saucepan, combine peas and ham with tomato juice, chopped onion, green chilies and garlic.
Heat until very hot.
Stir well.
Add cheese spread and Tabasco sauce.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve in chafing dish with taco or Frito chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
In a bowl, add soup and Cheez Whiz; stir well.
Add broccoli and rice.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sugar and margarine; set aside. Then mix milk and pudding mix by directions for pudding.
Next, mix cream cheese mixture and pudding thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer Oreos, then pudding mixture, starting first layer with Oreos and ending with Oreos.

title: tomato flower
directions: Rinse and drain lettuce.
Cut away core of tomato to hollow out.
Cut each tomato into 8 wedges; do not cut all the way through.
Place on lettuce leaf.
Fill tomato with cottage cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Pour French dressing over top.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Place beans in saucepan; add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook about 8 to 10 minutes or until almost tender.
Drain beans; return to pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until beans are tender.

title: minute steaks and gravy
directions: Brown minute steaks in a small amount of shortening after they have been floured, salted and peppered.
Place minute steaks in a large casserole.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over steaks.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
There will be a thick gravy to serve with the meat.

title: son's favorite casserole
directions: Slice 3 of the potatoes in bottom of a large casserole.
Add 1/2 of the sliced carrots.
The third layer is 1/2 of the hamburger.
On top of this, add 1/2 of the onions.
Each layer should be seasoned lightly.
Spoon half of the tomatoes on this and repeat layers, ending with tomatoes on top.
Be sure your casserole is large enough because it will prevent boiling over as the juices from the vegetables and the meat accumulate.
Bake in a 350° oven 2 hours.
Casserole is done when your fork pierces the carrots and potatoes easily.

title: raspberry float
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, juices and sugar.
Cool; do not chill.
Gelatin is not to congeal.
If it congeals, heat just enough to melt it to liquid.
When time to serve, pour mixture into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and frozen raspberries.
Stir until berries break apart and are partially thawed.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: quickie cookies
directions: Cut until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in 1 egg and 1 teaspoon flavoring.
Roll out on board and cut.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Bananas will not turn dark.
Can be served over ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, one cup at a time, with milk, flavoring and baking powder.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in baking dish.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; cover and blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Serve immediately.

title: betsy north's crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together on a cookie sheet until crackers are well coated.
Let air-dry and serve.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, sauce, bread crumbs, egg and seasonings together. Bake 1 hour and 375°.
Top with cheese and return to oven to melt.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg, vanilla, flour and nuts together. Roll in small balls, press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Simmer the first 9 ingredients together over medium heat, stirring, for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat; add onion, apples and celery.
Simmer until thick.

title: lemon supreme sponge cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix ingredients.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Use Pam spray on pans.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour, without opening door of oven.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice with 2 cups water.
Add oleo to cooked rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dutch apple-lemon custard pie(germany)
directions: Pare and grate the apple and grate also the rind of half a lemon.
Add the sugar and beaten eggs.
Bake, covered with pie crust in medium hot oven.
Sift with powdered sugar.

title: green rice
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Place in buttered (or sprayed) casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: puppy chow(snack)
directions: Melt together the first 3 ingredients.
Pour melted mix over cereal. Stir until all is covered.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Place in paper grocery sack.
(Double sack works best.)
Add powdered sugar and shake.
You may use more than 2 cups sugar.

title: dum dum salad
directions: Chill can of Eagle Brand milk.
Mix all ingredients together and chill in refrigerator.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the last 2, in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix crumbs and butter; top casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Cook lasagna as directed; drain.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, spread about 1 cup of sauce.
Then alternate layers of lasagna sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.	Reduce heat to 275 degrees and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: peg's ham loaf
directions: Mix crumbs and milk. Let stand 15 minutes. Combine ham and pork, then add crumbs and milk mixture. Add beaten eggs. Shape and place on rack in roasting pan. Spread all tomato soup over top of loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and sausage, add onion, green pepper.
Drain fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and then frost with cream cheese frosting.
Can also use pumpkin in place of carrots.

title: special k cookies
directions: Whip the butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla.
Mix with combined dry ingredients.
Carefully fold in cereal.
(I slightly crush the cereal before adding.)
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Let cool a little before removing from baking sheet.

title: elsie and daisy's peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, oleo and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter chips and marshmallows.
Add peanut butter and beat until glossy or until you know it's time to pour.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Mix in pecans and raisins.
Thoroughly combine eggs, sweet potatoes, oil and milk.
Make a well in center of flour mixture; add sweet potato mixture and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into a greased, floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1hour and 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove and let cool completely on wire rack.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Slice each layer in half. Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Beat well.
Spread each layer with filling.
Frost with fudge icing.

title: fruit pizza dessert
directions: Stir well, bring to boil in saucepan and cook 1 minute.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice 1 package Pillsbury sugar cookie mix in well-greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Allow to cool.
Spread over crust a mixture of 1 (8 ounce) softened cream cheese, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/2 cup sugar.
Top with sliced bananas, cantaloupe, peaches, apples, strawberries (fresh fruit).
Pour orange sauce over whole pizza.
Chill and serve pizza slices.

title: brussels sprouts scallop
directions: One handful of Forgiveness,

title: trail bologna
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and roll out into small rolls (about 2 inches in diameter).
Place the rolls into wax paper and plastic bags.
Put in the refrigerator for 24 hours (curing time). Then take the rolls and place on a cookie sheet and bake in the oven for 1 hour at 300°.
Remove from oven; drain the grease and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: escalloped chicken(mildred gregory)
directions: Melt fat or butter, add salt, pepper, milk, broth.
Stir in eggs.
Saute celery and onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over bread.
Mix well.
Add chicken and put in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in mixing bowl.
Heat margarine, Coca-Cola and cocoa to boiling point and pour over flour mixture. Mix together thoroughly.
Add milk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: quick rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups biscuit mix, sour cream, and butter; mix well.

title: pizza dough or bread(makes 3 large pizzas or 3 loaves of bread)
directions: Combine dry yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar and let set 10 minutes. Add warm water, warm milk and oil.
Add sugar, salt and eggs. Slowly add flour.
Mix together and dump on floured table.
Knead in flour until not sticky.
Rub oil over dough in 3 balls.
Cover with towel and let sit in warm area 1 hour; spread on pans.
Let rise.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.	In a saucepan, combine margarine, cocoa and cola and bring to a boil.

Pour over the flour mixture. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and mix well. Fold in marshmallows and mix well. Batter will be thin. Pour into a 9 x 13 greased cake pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until done. Ice while hot.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Boil only 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed; add nuts. Pour into buttered pan; let stand for 6 hours.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening, sugar and egg yolks in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add lemon juice to milk.
Add dry ingredients and liquid, alternately to creamed mixture.
Beat in the vanilla.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes, or until light brown.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage and let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out juice. Add carrot and pepper (chopped fine).
While cabbage is standing, make syrup of vinegar, water and sugar.
Add celery and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Let stand until lukewarm. Pour over cabbage mixture; place in freezer containers (can be frozen several times).

title: grandma dawson's fruit cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and shortening and cream.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: coconut pies(makes its own crust.)
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a bowl. Pour into 2 greased pie plates. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese with dry Italian dressing.
Add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in the remaining 1 cup chopped pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar, corn syrup and peanuts in 2-quart bowl. Cook for 4 minutes on high.
Stir well. Cook for 4 minutes longer. Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes more. Watch carefully as it will scorch if overcooked.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour at once into buttered cookie sheet. Cool at least 30 minutes.

title: pork and zucchini italiano(4 servings)
directions: Trim bone and fat from frozen pork chops and slice meat in 1/8-inch thick strips.
Saute onion and garlic in 1 teaspoon of oil in large skillet until soft.
Remove.
Add 2 teaspoons oil to skillet.
Cook and stir pork strips over medium heat, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add zucchini and saute all for 8 more minutes.
Stir in ketchup, spices and onion and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Add salt and pepper as desired.

title: broccoli and garlic pasta
directions: Cook 1/2 pound pasta until just tender.
Drain; rinse under cold water.
Drain again and reserve.

title: caramel dip
directions: Combine
sugar,
syrup, 3 tablespoons margarine and 1/2 cup cream;
bring
to
full
boil.
Gradually add rest of the margarine and cream to soft ball stage.
Add salt and vanilla. Serve with sliced apples and bananas.

title: dill dip
