directions: Mix well. Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook the chicken in boiling water until tender. Drain and cool.
Remove bones and cut in cubes.
Cook the macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Combine soup, milk, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and cheese and mix. Add the butter, chicken and macaroni and mix well.
Place in a baking dish and sprinkle with red pepper. Bake at 350° for 35 to 30 minutes. 8 to 10 servings.

title: classic apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with half the pastry.
In large bowl combine apples, sugar, flour, vanilla, cinnamon, ginger and mace; toss well to blend.
Transfer apple mixture to pastry lined pie pan and dot with butter.

title: quick chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze in hand-turned or electric freezer. Tastes similar to fudgsicle.

title: easy malt frosting
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and Crisco. Add slowly the milk and vanilla. Beat until stiff.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove meat from bones, combine cornbread crumbs, sliced bread crumbs, onion and about half of eggs and giblets in large mixing bowl.
Pour broth over ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture into baking dish. Place chicken and remaining eggs over mixture.
Pour cream of chicken soup over mixture.
Bake approximately 25 minutes at 350°.

title: judy's chicken and dumplings
directions: Put your rinsed off chicken into a large pot (5 to 6-quart). Cover with water.
Add poultry seasoning, several dashes of onion powder, 2 dashes of garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Boil until the chicken comes off the bone.
This takes about 1 1/2 hours in regular pot or 35 minutes in a pressure cooker.
Remove chicken from pot to drain.
Add soup and more seasonings, if you prefer, to the broth.
Simmer until soup is mixed in well with the broth.

title: peanut bars
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and cream.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and nuts.
Pour over hot crust; spread evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.
Drizzle with glaze.
Makes 60 bars.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add milk to mixture slowly. Beat egg yolks slightly and add to filling.
Stir in vanilla. Cook slowly in a double boiler until thick.
Pour in a baked pie crust and add meringue while filling is still hot.
Bake in a slow oven until light brown.

title: chicken & creole rice
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter in a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Sprinkle about 1 Tbsp. of Creole spice on top of butter.
(I prefer Konriko brand.)
Mix together cooked rice, cooked chicken pieces, soup, and 1 - 2 T. of Creole spice.
Pour on top of spiced butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Serves 8.

title: fish fillets au gratin
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Saute onion, celery and pepper. Blend in flour, stirring well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Add salt, pepper, thyme and hot sauce.
Place fish in buttered 8-inch square dish.
Cover with sauce.
Combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Pour over sauce. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until fish is done.
(May have to cover with foil the last 10 to 15 minutes to avoid top burning.) Serves 6.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Poke holes in cake with a fork.
Pour pineapple with juice over cake.
Mix together:
cream cheese, milk and pudding. Beat until smooth.
Spread over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut and decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Blend all but apples and roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with apples and bits of butter.
Roll like a jelly roll and cut in pieces about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Drop into boiling sauce and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: steamed broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli, garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Heat skillet (10-inch) to medium-high.
Add oil and stir-fry vegetables for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add water, cover pan and steam vegetables until tender.

title: crispy fried okra
directions: Wash okra by hand.
(Lightly rub pods with a paper towel under running water.)
Pat dry.
Cut okra into bite-sized pieces. Beat egg and pour onto okra and toss lightly until okra is coated. Sprinkle cornmeal onto okra and toss lightly until okra is covered.
Pour into a pre-heated skillet of oil (enough to coat bottom of skillet), on medium high.
Cook for a few minutes until okra is browned on one side and turn with spatula.
Cook until browned all over.
Lift out onto plate covered with paper towels and salt to taste.

title: savory grilled potatoes(yields 6 servings)
directions: Thinly slice 4 medium potatoes in greased baking dish or pan. Arrange layers of potatoes and flour, onion slices or grated onion.

Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper and dot with butter. Heat milk to scalding and pour over potatoes to barely cover. Bake about 30 to 40 minutes at 375° (covered), then add thickening of flour and milk that is well blended.
Let bake another 10 to 20 minutes, uncovered, until top is brown and potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, cocoa, salt, yolks and half and half until thick.
Remove from stove and add vanilla and oleo.
When oleo is melted, beat with a mixer to get the pudding smooth.
Pour into a baked pie shell, then add meringue and bake until a golden brown or you can let pudding cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: mrs. mondale's pumpkin bread
directions: Grease two small loaf pans and line with wax paper.
Mix dry ingredients.
Sift if you wish.
Add oil, eggs, pumpkin and water to dry ingredients.
Mix well at medium speed.
Add dates and nuts.
This batter is thin.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Truly outstanding.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Dip each tomato into boiling water for 15 to 30 seconds to aid in peeling.
Remove the skin, core the tomatoes and place in an 8-inch square dish.
Combine sugar and the next eight ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake well.
Pour over the tomatoes and chill for 8 hours.
Spoon the marinade over the tomatoes occasionally.
To serve, quarter tomatoes; place 3 or 4 wedges on lettuce leaves.

title: fruit balls
directions: Chop the first 4 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together (use hands) and form small balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. They do not spread, so you can put a lot on a cookie sheet to bake.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in saucepan over low heat or in microwave 30 seconds.
Mix in vanilla.
Pour over mixture of confectioners sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Mix quickly until smooth. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan; pat pecans over top.
Let stand until set; cut into squares.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a little salt and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh strawberry frost
directions: Wash strawberries; remove caps.
Mash or blend well.
Mix sugar, milk and vanilla. Stir in strawberries.
Scoop ice cream into tall glasses.
Pour strawberry mix over the ice cream. Garnish with whole uncapped strawberries.
Yields 7 servings.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Saute bacon and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Gently simmer until cheese is melted.

title: party wieners
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Mix mustard and jelly in saucepan.
Add wieners.
Cover and cook on low for 10 minutes. Serve on toothpicks.
Makes 3/4 cup sauce.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, peanut butter, sugars, egg, vanilla and orange juice. Add the flour, soda, baking powder and salt and mix well.
Take 1 teaspoon full of dough and roll into a ball, place on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork. Bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix eggs, milk, margarine, sugar, salt and pepper together. Pour over corn.
Bake at 350°
for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, eggs, water and lemon.
Add to sugar and cornstarch.
Cook slowly.
After cooking add butter and vanilla. Pour in cooked pie shell.

title: ginger drop cookies
directions: Cream lard and sugars; add egg and beat well.
Mix molasses and milk.
Mix dry ingredients and add creamed mixture alternately with molasses mixture.
Drop by teaspoon into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken rolls(serves 6)
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter in frying pan.
Add chicken, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend in chicken broth.
Mix in pan and simmer over low heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Fill each crescent roll with mixture.
Bake on greased baking sheet for 13 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and cream of mushroom soup.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk first.
Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, flour and vanilla.
Add scalded milk and put in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add sweet potatoes, oil and 2/3 cup of water.
Beat well and add eggs one at a time.
Add pecans, dates and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan and a small loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
This makes a very large cake.
Do not fill pans over 2/3 full!

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans; drain.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and tomato puree.
Season with salt, pepper and melted butter.
Turn into well buttered casserole.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven until vegetables are tender and brown.

title: pastel cookies
directions: Beat well the Butter, Sugar and Jello.
Beat in Egg and Vanilla.
Gradually add Flour and Baking Powder.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 approximately 10 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Cut green pepper into strips.
Add onion and green pepper to carrots; set aside.

title: stew-n-corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Empty stew into shallow 2-quart baking dish.
In mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add oil, milk and corn meal. Mix well.
Stir in cheese.
Pour over stew.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: For crust:
Mix graham crackers and one stick of melted butter.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk, then add eggs and melted butter. Add vanilla and pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dip for chips
directions: Saute onions.
Melt rest of ingredients together, stirring until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Cream until fluffy the butter, sugar, eggs, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Stir into cremed mixture the zucchini, vanilla, milk and the flour mixture.
Pour into two 9 inch floured pans and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Let stand five minutes and put on racks to cool.
When cool, ice with Cinnamon Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: apricot brandy bread
directions: Combine apricots and brandy.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Cream oleo.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg; mix well. Combine flour and next 6 ingredients.
Combine apricot mix and pecans with 1 cup flour; set aside.
Add rest of mixture alternating with applesauce.
Begin and end with flour mixture. Stir in rest of apricot mix.
Pour in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes for 40 minutes.
Cut up and add remaining ingredients.
Add a small amount of bacon grease.

title: meat loaf(aunt maggie and uncle dewitt whitman's)
directions: Mix all together and spoon into loaf pan.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Stir together Jell-O, water and ice cubes until ice cubes are melted, then soft set in refrigerator.
Then mix cranberry sauce, pineapple, walnuts, celery and apple into soft Jell-O.
Grease a six-cup mold with mayonnaise.
Make the night before serving.

title: quick spiced peaches
directions: You will need canning jars.

title: stewed tomatoes with dumplings
directions: In a saucepan, combine the tomatoes, sugar, salt, pepper and butter. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by serving spoon onto pan. (This dough maybe kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks.) Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or brown.

title: enchilada stack up
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, chilies, chili powder, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Stir in drained beans and olives.
Trim tortillas slightly smaller than diameter of crock-pot.
Add trimmings to meat mixture in bottom of cooker; top with tortilla.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Repeat layers until used up.
Pour tomato juice around edge of stack up. Cover; cook on low for 5 to 6 hours or on high heat for 2 1/2 hours.

title: raspberry squares
directions: Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 325° for 10 minutes.
Spread layer of jam over bottom.

title: cold asparagus salad
directions: Whisk together the vinegar, oil, garlic, mustard, thyme, sugar, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over mushroom slices. Refrigerate and marinate overnight.
Bring to room temperature before serving.

title: squash puffs
directions: Combine squash and egg and stir well.
Mix other ingredients and add to squash.
Drop into hot cooking oil and cook until golden brown.

title: chocolate irish cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch spring-form pan. In top of double boiler, over hot but not boiling water, melt chocolate chips and butter.
In large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks until very thick, about 5 minutes.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Stir in melted chocolate, pecans, 1/4 cup liqueur and vanilla.

title: cucumbers and onions
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thin.
Layer in dish; sprinkle each layer with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse cucumbers and dry on paper towels.
Slice onions thin.
Mix gently with cucumbers.
Beat mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until creamy.
Stir into mixed cucumbers and onions.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Fry
sausage scrambled in skillet until done.
Pour off any excess grease.
Place crescent roll dough on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Roll pieces very thin and arrange so that bottom
of pan is completely covered.
Press edges together at seams
so that
liquid mixture will not run under crust while cooking. Sprinkle
sausage
evenly
over finished crust.
Add Cheddar cheese and (thawed) hash brown potatoes.
Mix together eggs, milk,
salt
and
pepper.
Beat
slightly.
Pour liquid mixture over the other ingredients.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger and macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet until done. Add salt. Cook macaroni according to directions on package. In casserole dish, place one layer hamburger, tomato soup and macaroni, then add 3 to 4 slices of cheese. Repeat the process. Bake at 375° until cheese has melted.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Toast pecans in a slow oven.
Mix other ingredients in 2 or 3-quart boiler.
Cover (this is the secret).
Let it come to a good boil.
Remove cover and cook to soft candy stage.
Stir in and coat toasted nuts.
Pour out on waxed paper and separate while hot.

title: raspberry filled almond muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add milk, margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill lined muffin cups about 1/2 full.
Spoon 1 teaspoon raspberry jam into center of batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: congealed salad
directions: Make jello, when it starts to congeal, mix all ingredients. Put in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: peach, onion and bell pepper salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients; let sit in fridge at least 1/2 hour to blend flavors.

title: picante meat loaf(student favorite)
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Form into a loaf and place into a lightly greased baking dish.
Top with a little more picante sauce and grated cheese.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: funnel cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Test mixture to see if it flows through a funnel easily.
If too thick, add milk.
If too thin, add flour.
Heat oil.
Pour into funnel. Release batter into oil moving the funnel to make a spiral shape. Fry until golden, about 30 minutes.
Turn carefully.
Cook 1 minute more.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.
Makes 4 cakes.

title: hummingbird cake(note:  do not beat it as you mix it together.)
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream margarine and cheese thoroughly, then add confectioners sugar, small amount at a time, blending well between additions.
Thin to desired consistency with milk.
Spread between layers, on top and sides of cake.

title: heather's chicken frito casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter.
Add soups, milk, chicken and chiles; stir until warm.
In 3-quart casserole, put chicken mix and 1/2 chips.
Top with remaining chips and cheese. Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Bake at 325° (uncovered) for 30 minutes; let stand a few minutes before serving to set.
Serves 6.

title: mom's drop cakes
directions: Mix well and drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar on top.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients real well.
Shape into 1-inch ball. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sassy chicken
directions: Cook chicken in oil until tender.
Combine marmalade, onions, vinegar, soy sauce, cornstarch and ginger.
Remove chicken from skillet, put in marmalade mixture.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook 1 more minute.
Add grapes, chestnuts and chicken. Heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium-sized bowl; transfer to casserole.
Heat in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread on crackers (super with Triscuits!).

title: double chocolate macadamia nut cookies(microwave)
directions: Cream together the butter, white and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the vanilla and egg.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine
potatoes,
onion,
pickles, eggs and celery in large mixing
bowl.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Add to
potato mixture
until
potatoes are well coated.
May be served in salad bowl or platter lined with lettuce leaves.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Do not mix the cake mix according to the package.
Mix all 6 ingredients together, then add morsels and walnuts.
Bake in a tube pan, greased and floured, for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar on top of the cake when finished.

title: zesty shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and Miracle Whip until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill well before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: brownie trifle dessert
directions: Bake a box of brownie mix with walnuts according to directions. Cool. Break into small pieces. Make a small package of chocolate instant pudding. Use a glass trifle bowl. Layer chocolate pudding, brownies and a 12 ounce lite Cool Whip| two times. Sprinkle brownie crumbs on top.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Put noodles in boiler and bring to boil, then reduce heat to low after approximately 5 minutes.
When ground beef is browned, drain grease.
Then add tomato sauce, packet of spaghetti sauce mix, dash of garlic salt, dash of salt and pepper (to desired taste) and small chopped onion.
Simmer on low 5 to 10 minutes on stove top.

title: shrimp pilou
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients; bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.
Stir twice while cooking.

title: june's favorite salad
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and then sour cream until smooth.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops lightly on both sides.
Place in a casserole dish. In layers, cover each chop with cooked rice, tomato and onion slices or canned tomatoes, soup and water.
Lightly salt and pepper each layer.
Cover casserole and bake at 400° for about 1 hour, depending on size of chops.

title: satiny chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Blend in powdered sugar.
Set saucepan in bowl of ice water.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until frosting holds its shape.
Yields 3 cups.

title: low fat chocolate eclairs
directions: Layer 9 x 13 inch baking dish with crackers.
Mix pudding with milk and add
Cool Whip. Spread over crackers.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers.
Melt frosting in microwave for 1 minute and pour over top.

title: gooseberry salad(a tart companion for pork)
directions: Drain gooseberries, saving juice.
Mix sugar and berries; place over low heat just to melt sugar.
Add enough cold water to the gooseberry juice to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil and pour over gelatin.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Let set for a while and then add the banana and gooseberries.

title: onions au gratin
directions: If using fresh onions, parboil for 10 minutes; drain and place in au gratin dish. Melt butter or margarine; stir in flour and mix until smooth.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly. Cook until thick; remove from heat and add grated cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over onions.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: chocolate rich crescent croissants
directions: Separate dough into
triangles.
Press	each to enlarge slightly.
Spread butter on each triangle.	Place equal amount of chocolate on shortest
side
of
each
triangle.
Roll
up, starting at shortest side.	Place
rolls
point
side
down on ungreased baking sheet; curve into crescent shape.	Brush each roll with beaten egg;
sprinkle each with almonds.	Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Let
them cool for a while. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: hamburgers and onion gravy
directions: Mix meat with egg, crumbs, seasoning and half of the onion soup mix.
Make patties and fry until brown on both sides.
Remove when brown.
Add the flour to frypan and stir until it browns lightly.
Put in remaining onion soup mix and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes.
Put meat back in gravy and cover.
Cook another 5 or 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: camp stew
directions: Cut pork and beef into hunks.
Cook with chicken breast in a large container.
Cover well with water.
When tender, let cool and skim off grease.
Cook onions and potatoes together.
Use liquid from the meat.
Cook tomatoes a few minutes and mash.
Tear meat into small pieces.
Mix meat, potatoes, onions and tomatoes.
Make sure there is enough liquid.
Add hot sauce and 1 tablespoon "Moore" sauce.
Simmer on low 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add bread. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake in pan of water at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip muffins(with chocolate streusel)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line twelve medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with cooking spray.
Combine flour, oats, chocolate chips, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine buttermilk, honey, oil and egg; blend well.
Add to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir just until
moistened.
Do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Sprinkle with streusel, patting gently.
Bake 20-22 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool muffins in pan on wire rack 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Pour into large glass baking dish.
Place raw chicken pieces on top, bone side down. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add a little paprika. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish which has been greased.
Layer browned sausage over bread; sprinkle the cheese and mushrooms over top.
Combine the beaten eggs, dry mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight.
When ready to bake, combine the soup and remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over all.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix and jell the Jell-O, hot water, orange juice, oranges and pineapple.
Cook pineapple juice, egg and sugar until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour on top of Jell-O.
Let set 1 hour before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until tender. Add broccoli and rice.
Melt cheese on top of stove in a saucepan.
Add soup to cheese.
Place broccoli mixture in a casserole dish.
Pour cheese and soup mixture over top.
Then top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain well.
While noodles are cooking, melt butter in frying pan over high heat until lightly browned.
Add 1/2 cup of the cream and boil until slightly thickened.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add noodles and gently mix.
Then add half the cheese and 1/2 cup remaining cream.
Lift and mix pasta.
Repeat with remaining cheese and cream.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: gladys' imperial crab
directions: Mix crabmeat, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and put in individual shells.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs, paprika and a dab of butter (or margarine) on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: huevos rancheros light
directions: Combine egg whites, yolks, milk, salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Spray nonstick pan with olive oil Pam; heat on low.
Add egg mixture; scramble lightly until set.
Serve with green chili sauce and salsa with flour tortillas.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
In small bowl, combine milk, egg and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients all at once, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in blueberries and spoon into muffin pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Makes 6 large or 12 small muffins.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add nuts, oranges and pineapple.
Put in pie crust and let stay in refrigerator awhile before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bill's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Vary to your taste.
May be stored in refrigerator 6 weeks.
Great on chicken, pork, etc.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let marinate overnight in refrigerator. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Put on water to boil for spaghetti while you heat one tablespoon oil on medium heat.
Cube Spam into 1/2-inch chunks. Place in oil, stirring constantly until warm and browned.
Heat broth.
Drain noodles.
Place into four bowls.
Top with Spam and chopped green onions.
Divide and pour broth over noodles in bowls.
Season to taste with Worcestershire sauce and serve.

title: sponge cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir. Beat 3 egg yolks in large bowl at high speed for 1 minute, gradually adding 3/4 cup sugar until egg yolks are thick and pale (about 5 minutes). Add vanilla and water, beating at low speed.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture until well blended.

Beat 5 egg whites at high speed until foamy, gradually adding remaining 1/4 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time. Beat until stiff peaks are formed. Gently fold 1/4 of the egg white mixture into the batter, then fold in the remainder. Pour batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Invert pan and cool for 45 minutes, then remove cake from tube pan.
Makes 10 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: banana shrub(slush)
directions: Mix water and sugar in a pan; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Mix a small amount of pineapple and orange juice with the banana in a blender until smooth.
Add the rest of the juices and blend until smooth.
Add juice mixture to water and sugar mixture.
Freeze in ice cube trays.
One half hour before serving, set out and pour ginger ale on top.

title: honey's purple salad
directions: Prepare 1 package of Jell-O according to package directions. Add pineapple and pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Congeal.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour pork and beans into medium size casserole dish.
Put bean and bacon soup into colander and wash with hot water.
Combine the two beans in dish and mix in other ingredients.
Lay bacon strips on top of mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: scalloped celery
directions: Blanch almonds in oleo. Add bread crumbs and brown. Combine other ingredients and pour into buttered baking dish. Cover with almonds and crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hobos
directions: Cut okra and
potatoes as for frying.
Cut onion up and mix to okra and potatoes;	meal all and fry.
Salt to taste.

title: banana mamas(jamaican cocktail)
directions: Combine in a blender with a few ice cubes.
Blend briefly. Serves 4.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Boil the fryer (reserve stock).
Remove meat from bone and cut into small pieces.
Combine liquids and stir in chicken, chiles and salt.
Cut tortillas in half.
Dip into hot shortening a few seconds.
Put a layer of tortillas in bottom of casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Spoon on a layer of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and onion.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° until bubbling, 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all together.
Put in oven for 3 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Add vanilla, flour, syrup and nuts. Pour into sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Steam the vegetables, then cook chicken (boil).
Chop celery and onions, then after chicken is cooked, take bones out.
Mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake pie at 350° until crust is brown (about 30 minutes or so).

title: shrimp or crawfish etouffe
directions: Melt
stick of butter in a saucepan; add onion, pepper, garlic and parsley flakes.
Simmer until onions are clear; add tomato sauce, 1/2 can of water and meat.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until meat is done.
Serve over rice.

title: cauliflower broccoli bake
directions: In a large saucepan, cook cauliflower and broccoli according to package directions.
Drain; remove vegetables from pan.
In the same pan, combine corn, soup, cheese, mushrooms, onion and herb. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in cauliflower and broccoli. Transfer mixture to a 2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine; combine with crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until bubbly and crumbs are browned.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: finger jello(childrens recipe)
directions: In medium bowl, combine Knox gelatin and Jello,
Add boiling water and stir until Jello is dissolved.
Pour into oblong pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate chicken wings at least 1 hour. Arrange wings on a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, basting 2 or 3 times.

title: franks and kraut
directions: Brown onions in little fat. Add catsup, water, brown sugar and mustard. Simmer 5 minutes. Put sauerkraut in a 2-quart baking dish. Slice franks into inch pieces and arrange them on top of the kraut. Pour sauce over all. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: incredible edibles
directions: Crush cookies (including icing centers) in food processor or blender until mixture resembles dirt.
Set aside.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and store.
Put 2 heaping tablespoons in mug and add boiling water.
May use more or less of powdered mixture.

title: boston creme cherry pie
directions: Cream the cheese, vanilla, sugar and nuts.
Then pour into prepared crust (dust crust lightly with egg white; bake at 350° for 3 minutes.)
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly brown. Let cool.
Add cherries; let cool in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and serve!

title: cherry cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add gradually.
Add pecans, dates and cherries.
Make balls about the size of a walnut and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Lay balls on a cookie sheet. Pat slightly with hand.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: oriental roast hen
directions: Rinse hen in tepid water.
Pat dry and shake with flour in plastic bag.
Place hen halves, skin side up, in shallow nonstick baking dish and bake in a 450° oven until skin is golden and fat is melted (10 minutes or more).
Pour off and discard melted fat from pan.
Lower oven heat to 300°.
Arrange apricots under and around hen halves.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over and around hen.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake about 50 minutes or until hen is very tender.
Remove foil.
Raise heat to 375°.
Continue to bake until skin is crispy and liquid has evaporated into a thick sauce.
Place hen halves on serving plates and glaze with apricot sauce.
Plan to double recipe as this freezes nicely.
Nice for company.
Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Scald milk.
Add the sugar and salt to the milk; stir until both are thoroughly dissolved.
Add the cream.
Stir in the vanilla.
Cool.
Turn into freezer.
Makes 2 quarts.
Add your favorite flavorings, such as:
bananas for banana ice cream or maraschino cherries (chopped up with the juice) for cherry flavoring.

title: great cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still hot, after taken from oven, poke holes with wooden spoon handle all over cake.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk and caramel ice cream topping over top of cake.
Let cool. Frost with Cool Whip and top with crushed Heath bars. Refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place on top of stove and melt together.
Grease pan and pour in.
Place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Mix and marinate meat overnight. Bake on a rack at 350° for 25 minutes each side.

title: tip beef roast and rice
directions: Take the broth from roast and add thickening for gravy.
May add 1/2 teaspoon or less of instant coffee for coloring.
When ready to eat, put rice on plate first.
Add beef and gravy.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: stir and roll biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Pour oil and milk into cup without stirring.
Pour all at once into flour.
Stir with a fork. Pat out on sheet of waxed paper.
Cut with a cutter.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/4 inch thick.
Arrange slices close together in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla and sugar in mixer bowl until smooth.
Spread over cookie layer.
Layer pie filling, pineapple and bananas over creamed layer.
Chill until serving time.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Sift flour with soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill in refrigerator.
Roll into nut size balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Stores well in airtight container. Makes 12 dozen cookies.

title: nachos
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add flour; mix thoroughly.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and water; cook for 10 minutes, or until thickens. Layer chips on cookie sheet; pour meat sauce on top.
Grate cheese on top of meat sauce.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Delicious!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs with oil and sugar. Add dry ingredients a little at a time. Add zucchini, nuts and raisins. Grease 2 loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with marshmallow cream and a few drops of food coloring.
Refrigerate or keep cool.
Dip with fruit.
